title: lo country boil
directions: In a large kettle, place potatoes into salted boiling water; simmer 1 hour, then add corn-on-the-cob to kettle.
Bring back to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes, then add onions and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes. Right before serving, add shrimp and crab legs.
Cook until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Serve in a large bowl or kettle.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine cookies and margarine.
Pat firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Beat until smooth and add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
In a small bowl, toss together 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill then remove from pan and enjoy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken.
Chop the celery and water chestnuts.
Sliver almonds.
Chop eggs.
Soup is added along with chopped onion and pimento.
Mix garlic powder and herbs in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Fold into mixture and bake with topping of grated cheese and crushed potato chips at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter 11 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add chips, cream and nuts.
Pour up into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: better than sex pudding
directions: Blend butter and flour; pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake crust 20 minutes at 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 10x sugar; add Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour on top of cream mix.
Chill and add a dab of Cool Whip.

title: onion soup gratene
directions: Cut 4 (1-inch) slices French bread; may serve rest of bread. In saucepan over medium heat, cook onions in butter and sugar for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour; blend well.
Add water, wine and undiluted beef broth.
Heat to boiling, simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Put in bowls.
Top with bread and cheese.
Bake in 425° oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat graham cracker crust
directions: Cook margarine over low heat until melted.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Press crust onto bottom and sides of pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Best after refrigerating for a few hours.

title: southern barbecue
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
To this mixture, add brown sugar, vinegar and table mustard and simmer carefully for about 1/2 hour.
Then add the ketchup, molasses and tomato paste.
Cook mixture for at least 1/2 hour watching carefully as it scorches easily.

title: oysters "johnny reb"
directions: Place layer of oysters in bottom of greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of parsley, shallots, seasonings, lemon juice, butter and crumbs.
Make another layer of the same ingredients, ending with crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: bran muffins(diet)
directions: Sift flour and soda together into medium-sized mixing bowl. Add bran flakes.
Combine buttermilk, egg, margarine and sugar substitute.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients, stirring only enough to mix ingredients slightly.
Add raisins.
Spoon batter into nonstick muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease small muffin tins.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs; mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift flour, then measure.
Add spices to flour.
Add milk and flour (alternating) to other ingredients and fold in nuts and raisins. Don't overmix.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: marrioes potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes for 15 minutes.
Drain off water.
Cut potatoes in half.
Lay flat side down on baking.
Spread with butter and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix all together.
Press into a greased pie pan.

title: low-fat blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg whites with a fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients; stir into egg mixture just until flour is moistened. Add berries.
Batter should be thick and lumpy.
Do not overmix. Pour into cupcake papers in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dressing
directions: Beat cottage cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve on salad greens, tomatoes, steamed asparagus, broccoli or sweet potatoes.

title: sourdough doughnuts
directions: Mix together sourdough starter, milk and 1 1/2 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and oil, beating well.
Blend together in a small bowl the sugar, salt, baking soda and 1/2 cup flour.
Add to sourdough mixture and mix well.
Turn out onto 1 cup of flour on bread board.
Knead lightly, working most of the flour into the dough.
Dough will be very soft.
Place dough in well-greased bowl and turn once to grease top.
Cover with waxed paper and set in warm place to rise until doubled.

title: warm appetizer
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; spread on party ryes.
Broil for 30 seconds or until mixture bubbles.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and pat potatoes dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way through.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Place pie filling in pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and vanilla until smooth and creamy. Lower oven temperature to 350°. Gently spoon cheese mixture over cherries. Bake 30 minutes. Cool. Spread sour cream over top of cooled pie, sprinkle with nutmeg and refrigerate until served.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and set aside.
Scald milk. Add shortening, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add egg and yeast mixture.
Beat.
Knead in flour.
Let rise once (about 1 hour).

title: easy italian casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven or large pot, bring the water to a boil.
Add beef, veal and pork.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until the meat changes color and the fat rises to the top.
Pour into a colander and drain.
Return the meat to the Dutch oven or pot and cook over medium-high heat for 10 minutes or until remaining liquid evaporates and meat begins to brown.
Add the onions and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Add the chili powder, paprika, peppers, oregano, cumin and rosemary.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add the beans and tomato sauce.
Reduce the heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with the coriander.
Serves 12.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Mix well.
Knead by hand until blended. Shape dough into small balls.

title: biscuits
directions: Blend flour, Crisco, salt and baking powder well, then add approximately 1 cup milk.
Make dough sticky, then put on floured board and knead 12 times.
Pat or roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cook at 425° until tops are golden brown, approximately 12 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with bacon just before serving.

title: sesame seed chicken
directions: Cut chicken wings at joints into 3 pieces.
Combine rest of ingredients and marinate wings (or halved chicken thighs) for at least 2 hours.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar. Gradually cream together until light. Add eggs and beat; add bananas and beat again. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Pour into greased 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix in brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat.
Sift and add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nutmeats.
Spread on greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pan or larger.
Bake at 325° for about 2 minutes.
Watch closely and do not overbake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in top of double boiler until cheese melts and mixture bubbles.
Line casserole with Fritos and pour half mixture over.
Repeat chips and chicken.
Top with favorite grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: "it must be sunday" waffles(a family favorite!)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and oil.
Pour into the flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and fold into mixture.
Use mixture in waffle iron.
Yield:
8 waffles.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and butter over low heat; cool.
Add marshmallows and pecans to chocolate mixture.
Shape into 2 rolls 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
Refrigerate.
When thoroughly chilled, slice rolls into 1/2-inch slices.
Yield:
about 3 dozen cookies.

title: raisin energy snack
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Eat now or on a hike.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Mix together in a bowl the undiluted soups and the taco sauce.
Crush Doritos.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of hamburger, a layer of soup mix and a layer of crushed Doritos.
Repeat layers, ending with Doritos. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and return to warm oven for about 2 minutes.

title: greens and grapes salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk salt, pepper, oil, lemon juice and honey until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat. Serves 6.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cream pie
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Slice fresh strawberries and rhubarb (either fresh or frozen) and gently add to the mixture.
Place mixture in pie shell.
Stir together 1/2 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie.
Wrap edges of pie with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes (425 calories, 17 g fat).

title: frozen snow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.

title: peas in casserole
directions: Cook peas 3 minutes and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in the soup, water chestnuts and pimientos; mix well.
Bake in casserole for about 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with onion rings. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, until onion rings are brown.

title: holiday brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Let cool.
In separate bowl, mix next 5 ingredients.
Gradually add flour.
Beat until smooth.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting 2-inch squares from pan. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough out on pizza pan.
Cook at temperature noted on package.
However, undercook dough.
Do not let it get too brown or crunchy.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cooked dough.
Top with fruit of your choice.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto aluminum foil or wax paper.
Let cool, then eat.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press 3 or 4 more M&M's into each cookie.

title: easy sweet-sour chicken
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken.
Sometimes, I use boned breasts.
This makes enough to pour over one 8 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish full of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut-pecan bars
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar until fluffy.
Gradually stir in 1 cup flour until well blended.
Pat evenly in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Prebake in a preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes or until firm to touch.
Remove from oven.
Meanwhile beat eggs until light colored and add remaining 1 cup brown sugar, salt and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Fold in remaining 2 tablespoons flour, pecans and coconut.
Spread over crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely and cut into thirty-two 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in 2 to 3 quarts boiling water.
Cool and dice. Add chicken and mushrooms to soup over low heat.
Add browned onion and green pepper.
Using water from the chicken, bring to a boil.
Cook noodles to appropriate tenderness.
Layer in a casserole dish the noodles, soup mixture and cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: the best chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix with mixer on medium speed.
Heat oven to 375°.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar, flour and soda.
Add spices, then add applesauce and raisins.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done. Makes 1 loaf.

title: whipped cheese topping
directions: *May substitute strawberry jam for the last 3 ingredients.

title: easy pumpkin squares
directions: Set aside one cup of mix.
Add 1/2 cup melted butter and 1 egg to cake mix.
Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix can of pumpkin with evaporated milk and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture. Mix the 1 cup of cake mix that you set aside with the sugar, cinnamon and soft butter.
Crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
A great alternative for kids during the holidays.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight containers. Use 2 heaping teaspoons to each cup of hot water.

title: icebox cake
directions: Line pan with vanilla wafers, then put a layer of bananas, layer of pineapple, layer of coconut and layer of pecans.
Take juice from pineapple, butter, sugar and eggs, cook this 3 or 4 minutes, then pour over the layers and refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve it with whipped cream.
Makes about 10 nice servings.

title: chocolate covered pecan candy
directions: Toast pecans and put in food processor or chop finely.
Melt almond bark/chocolate bark in saucepan.
Stir pecans into melted chocolate.
Spoon out on wax paper or on aluminum foil.
Put in freezer for about 30 seconds or until chocolate sets.

title: slaw
directions: Combine the oil, vinegar and celery seed and boil for one minute.
Cool and add to the first mixture and stir several times until mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: speedies with venison
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except meat. Cut meat into small cubes.
Pour ingredients over meat and mix well.
Let marinate overnight in refrigerator. Cook on skewers over hot coals. These will keep in marinade 7 to 10 days without spoiling.

title: rich rolls
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
After 5 minutes, stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add 1/2 of the flour.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in a warm greased bowl.
Brush very lightly with melted fat.
Let rise about 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 1/2 to 3/4 hour or until double. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy strudel
directions: Cut oleo into flour; add egg yolks, vinegar and water and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Roll out on floured board until just a little thicker than pie crust.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a trifle bowl or other decorative glass bowl, crumble 1/4 of cake, following with each of the other ingredients except cherries.
Repeat, finishing with whipped topping and cherries.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Topping:
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup pecans; set aside.

title: hamburger rice hot dish
directions: Fry up hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for (deep pan) 1 1/2 hours, (shallow pan) 1 hour.
Or microwave at High for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet sausage dinner
directions: Cook sausage in 12-inch skillet at medium-high heat 2 minutes. Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender, about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add rice, mix well and add remaining ingredients, except pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in green pepper.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and shortening; add enough milk to make consistency of biscuit dough.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spread blackberries sprinkled with 2 cups sugar; drop dough on top by large spoonfuls.
Bake at 325° until browned on top, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Put cooked, sliced carrots in a bowl.
Add onions which have been cut into 1/2 cross-section.
Set aside.
Combine tomato soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, green pepper and mustard.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from burner.
Pour this mixture over carrots and onions.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours. Salad will keep fresh for one week or more.

title: ice cream pudding pie
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat together the flour, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan drop(cookie)
directions: Fold together sugar, pecans, cinnamon, vanilla, and salt. Fold in egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake in slow oven (325°) approximately 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen cookies.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Add salt, 2 dashes of pepper and spoon of butter.
Make sure you've got plenty of water in it. Brown meat.
Drain and pour in your pot of cabbage.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers, drain. Add beef mixture, macaroni, 3/4 cup sauce and water. Pour into a casserole dish, add cheese.
Add pepperoni and pour on rest of sauce. Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pizza mexicana
directions: On each tortilla, place 1/8 of ingredients and oregano and garlic powder to taste.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 400° oven about 7 minutes, then let top brown in broiler about 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: super easy fat-free banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
In separate bowl, mix applesauce, egg substitute and bananas with mixer or by hand. Slowly add dry ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, sprayed with cooking spray for 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat butter, sugars, and vanilla until creamy. Add eggs one at a time. Gradually beat in flour. Stir in remainder of ingredients. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 9 to 11 minutes until golden brown.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream the cheese and add tuna. Add 1/4 cup nuts and 1/4 cup parsley.
Mix well and form into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts and parsley. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: diabetic apple-raisin crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 3 tablespoons apple juice concentrate and oats; mix lightly and set aside.
Combine apples and raisins in large bowl; set aside.
Combine cornstarch, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in medium bowl; mix well. Blend in remaining 1 cup apple juice concentrate.
Add to apple mixture; mix lightly to coat.
Spoon into shallow 1 1/2-quart or 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine flour and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add oat mixture; mix lightly.
Stir in walnuts, if desired; sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm, at room temperature, or chilled with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pumpkin pie(in honor of "expresson")
directions: Stir together 1 slightly beaten egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pie spice.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.

title: ho bo beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cook until meat is done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese; mix well.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole or pan.
Bake in oven at 350° until almost done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar and whip in eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Line bottom of ungreased tube cake pan with wax paper.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until done. Cool in pan.

title: "wet" chocolate cake
directions: Make chocolate cake according to recipe in sheet pan.
While still warm, make icing.
Combine cocoa, sugar, butter or oleo, corn syrup and Pet milk; mix in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil slowly, stirring now and then until small amount dropped in water forms a soft ball.
Add vanilla and salt.
Poke holes in sheet cake and frost with this icing while hot.
Icing is thin.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and boils one minute. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into serving dish or individual dishes.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn about 3 minutes; cut from cob.
Put cabbage, onions and peppers through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Combine all vegetables.
Blend salt, flour, turmeric, sugar and mustard; add vinegar gradually.
Bring to boil and add vegetables.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix water, Cream of the West cereal, salt, honey and molasses. Cook 10 minutes and let cool to 120°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place eggs in mixing bowl.
Add syrup, sugar, vanilla, butter and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir 2 cups flour, corn meal, yeast and salt together in a mixing bowl.
Add water, butter and molasses.
Beat hard for 3 minutes.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough. Turn out onto a floured board.
Knead until no longer sticky. Place in a greased bowl.
Butter top of dough lightly.
Cover with a clean towel.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch dough down.
Turn onto a floured board; knead 1 to 2 minutes.
Shape into 2 balls.
Place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until doubled, 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until they sound hollow.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a nice size casserole dish. Stir well.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together in any order, grease two 9-inch cake pans.
Pour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; 50 to 60 minutes if using a Bundt pan or 25 to 30 minutes for a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: confetti mix
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl and it's ready to eat.

title: "itillian chicken"
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Arrange chicken in dish. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon Parmesan, 1/2 tablespoon garlic powder and 1/2 tablespoon oregano.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour off any liquid in baking dish, then pour the remaining mixture and return to oven.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve over bed of egg noodles.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Combine juice, vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spices and add enough boiling water to make 2 cups liquid.
Stir in jello.
Add sliced peaches. Cool until set.

title: grape, blueberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
In a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, mix blueberries and pineapple. Pour Jell-O mixture over this and chill until set.

title: spanish rice
directions: In greased frying pan, stir rice until it turns golden brown. Add chopped onion, tomato sauce and 1 can hot water.
Cover and simmer until all ingredients evaporate and rice is dry.

title: taco meat filling
directions: Saute meat in hot skillet until well cooked. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Simmer and remove from stove; drain meat in large sifter to remove extra fat. Place 2 tablespoons filling in taco shell with chopped tomato and taco sauce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti per directions on box.
Drain, then mix in other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, be sure to mix well!

title: hot dip
directions: Heat and use for dip.

title: adobe stew
directions: Warm the oil in medium saucepan.
Add onion and garlic; saute for 3 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Break up tomatoes with spoon.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer until the chicken is cooked through.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Empty peanut butter into a large mixing bowl and add butter (softened) and sugar.
Mix until soft and creamy.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Dip balls into the chocolate.
Let dry on wax paper to harden.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Thaw out the cranberries and raspberries.
Put in blender and chop.
After a minute or two, then put the blender on whip, then mix with whole almonds.
Put in the refrigerator and let chill.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add the other ingredients except eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over egg yolks which have been slightly beaten and cook a few minutes more. Cool slightly.
Pour into baked shell and cover with meringue made with egg whites and 6 tablespoons confectioners sugar. Bake in moderate oven until meringue is lightly browned.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Let simmer 2 to 3 hours.
For variety, add 1 can drained bean sprouts.

title: peanut butter honey snacks
directions: Mix together; form into small balls.
Refrigerate until firm. This is a snack kids really like if they like peanut butter.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and 1/4 cup milk, flour and cocoa.
I mix all this in the blender.
Heat rest of milk and add butter and salt.
Stir first mixture into hot milk and add vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Serves 6.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended and chill. Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add cracker crumbs and mix by hand. Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Stir in pineapple. Fold in whipped topping. Place ladyfingers around the sides and on the bottom of a greased 9 inch spring-form pan. Pour filling into pan. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Remove sides of pan. Top with strawberries.

title: boiled chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour until cool (if you can).

title: brandon's favorite cheese sandwich
directions: Take 2 slices of bread, put butter on 1 side of each slice of bread. Put cheese in between non-buttered sides. Put together and grill on low heat until bread is browned on each side or until cheese is melted. May also add green chilies or favorite lunch meat.

title: tex mex dip
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer ingredients as follows:
bean dip spread on bottom as first layer.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper; spread mixture as second layer.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; spread as third layer.
Sprinkle chopped onions, chopped tomatoes, chopped olives and shredded cheese on top.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and serve immediately.

title: yum-yums
directions: Put in saucepan butter, chocolate and evaporated milk.
Melt over low heat.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
While cooking, crush graham crackers in bowl.
Add marshmallows and nuts.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix well flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour mixture into melted butter but don't stir.
Add peaches.
Don't stir!! Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over peaches.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, celery salt, paprika and pepper in paper bag. Beat milk and egg together.
Shake 3 or 4 pieces of chicken in bag at a time.
Dip in egg-milk mixture, then shake again in bag. Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place chicken in single layer with skin side down in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake about 25 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: ham and noodle dinner
directions: Cook noodles and peas in sauce pan for 8-10 minutes or follow package directions.
Drain.
Return to sauce pan on low heat.
Add rest of ingredients and toss until well blended and heated through.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Butter or grease Bundt pan or funneled pan.
Place 22 frozen bread rolls in pan.
Pour melted margarine over frozen rolls. Pour brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans over rolls.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Store in oven overnight to rise.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except almonds; mix well.
Spread on ungreased 9-inch pie pan or 1-quart shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until hot.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and chili powder; drain.
Add enchilada sauce and cook down so there is very little liquid.
Remove from heat and add Longhorn cheese.
Stir until melted.
Spread meat mixture on 12 flour tortillas.
Roll up and place in baking dish.

title: strawberry topping
directions: Bring strawberries and
sugar
to boil.
Boil 1 minute, then put in Certo and let
boil
minutes.
Put
in jars and seal. You can use hot
water
bath
for a couple minutes, but not too long.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in large saucepan; place over medium heat.
Stir until margarine has melted and sugar has dissolved.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until mixture reaches 234° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts. Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate until completely set up.
Cut into small squares.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Pour water over raisins.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 3 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Cool.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Blend until well mixed.
Add raisin liquid.
Blend.
Add raisins; stir by hand.
Mix in flour and soda, then add oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven about 15 minutes or until done.

title: california chicken(tuna casserole)
directions: Layer in 8 1/2 x 12-inch casserole.
Pour soup, with just enough milk added to make just liquid enough to pour, over all. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: anita's party pizzas
directions: Cook sausage, drain.
Mix sausage, cheese, catsup, Worcestershire and salt.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat brown sugar and water to boiling.
Pour over mixture of sifted flour, cornstarch and white sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour into baked crust and cover with meringue.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Drain salmon and remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon into small chunks.
Add onion and macaroni; mix well.
Stir in soups, salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Combine butter and crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: alfalfa layered salad
directions: Layer in a large, round, glass bowl the following ingredients in the order listed:
alfalfa sprouts, green onions, celery, water chestnuts and peas.

title: cabbage slaw(make 2 days ahead)
directions: Cut cabbage into thick slices or strands.
Slice cucumbers thin.
Cut peppers into chunks or slices.
Slice carrots on diagonal.
Cut onion into rings and then in half.

title: steamed asparagus with roasted red pepper sauce
directions: Steam asparagus until tender.
Peel and seed roasted peppers and place in blender.
Mix remaining ingredients with peppers and puree for 30 seconds.
Strain the sauce through sieve.
Arrange asparagus on large platter and drizzle with sauce.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Cook 45 minutes at 300°.
This recipe was handed down from Mrs. Birdie Phillips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup nuts. Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: barbecued corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove husks from corn.
Wash corn.
Wrap corn in foil paper, smothered with butter and sprinkled with salt and pepper. Barbecue them for about 1 hour, turning them occasionally.
When done, sprinkle them with chili powder.
Yummy!

title: cindy's burger bundles
directions: Mix milk and ground chuck.
Divide into 4 flat patties.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in the center of each patty.
Mold meat around stuffing in center of patty to form a ball.
Place in a shallow square baking dish and cover with soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste several times.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan; then spread graham cracker crumbs. Then add coconut, etc., all in layers using Eagle Brand milk last, undiluted.
Do not mix.
Place in preheated oven at 325° and bake for 20 minutes.
Then place in refrigerator until cool.
Cut in squares.

title: banana tea muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Mix together egg, shortening and bananas.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing only enough to dampen all flour.
Turn into well-greased small muffin pans and bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for about 20 minutes or until muffins are done.
Serve muffins hot or cold.
Makes 16 small muffins.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Prepare fresh green beans.
Cut into one-inch pieces.
Cook until tender.
Toss beans, oil, vinegar, onion, salt, garlic and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.

title: molasses cream cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses, mix thoroughly.
Blend in all dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut sized ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet (do not flatten).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done (centers will be slightly soft).

title: blueberry delite
directions: Melt margarine in bowl.
Add flour and pecans.
Press mixture into 8 x 10-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream the cheese with butter; stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Blend well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough completely around each olive (that you have drained and dried well), completely covering the olive.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate (grass roots) pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°
and
bake
for
minutes.
To make two pies, double
all ingredients
except
evaporated milk.
Just add a whole can of milk.
Do not double milk!

title: caraway puffs
directions: In large bowl combine first 3 ingredients.

title: jiffy spanish rice
directions: In a
3-quart
casserole,
crumble
beef.
Microwave at High 5 to	7
minutes,
stirring after 3 minutes.	Drain.	Add rice, tomatoes,
onion, chili powder, salt and pepper;
cover. Microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes; stir well.
Let stand, covered, for about 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple stack pie
directions: You put cake mix in skillet and make about 2 or 3 layers and then you cook the apples until they're good and soft to where you mash them. Then you put some sugar until it is sweet enough for you. Then about a tablespoon of spice.

title: pork chops over rice
directions: Brown chops.
Spread rice in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1 teaspoon onion soup mix.
Sprinkle rest on rice.
Add 3 cups water and mushroom juice to the rice.
Put the chops over rice.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from heat for 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: turkey glaze
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer one minute.
Brush on turkey 1 time during cooking time.
This glaze seals in moistness and
gives the turkey a beautiful golden color and delicious flavor.

title: sugar-free applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins and water together until tender in covered pan until water evaporates.
Add dates and shortening to hot raisins; stir until blended.
Add applesauce, vanilla, sweetener and pineapple.
Add eggs.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to raisin mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Serves 16.

title: banana raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix raisin bran and milk; set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add this to bran mixture.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Put chopped artichokes in a bowl. Add mayonnaise and cheese and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and flatten.
Sprinkle top with more grated cheese and top with a layer of flavored bread crumbs.
Put a couple of pats of butter on top and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Stir in milk, butter and vanilla until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips. Spread in an ungreased, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa on top. Place in oven; pour boiling water over the top. Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving. Serve with ice cream or whipped topping. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 15 minutes.

title: louisiana peach bread
directions: Place peaches and 6 tablespoons sugar in container of electric blender.
Process until pureed (yields about 2 1/4 cups).

title: chicken wing dings
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together for a marinade.
Cut chicken wings apart. Poke with a sharp fork. Soak in marinade in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in single layer with a small amount of marinade poured over them. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash loaves
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, squash and oil; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves; add to first mixture, then add nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, cheese, pimiento, parsley, green pepper, bread crumbs and salt in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and milk; pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage crunch salad
directions: Toss everything together.
Just before serving, add dressing.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and oil to a quick boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Drain canned vegetables and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour liquid over vegetables and let set overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Lightly brown pork chops in small amount oil; drain on paper towel.
Place in oblong casserole dish.
Drain potatoes and pour over chops.
In small bowl, mix all other ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and thoroughly heated.
Can be prepared overnight and baked in morning.

title: coconut cake
directions: Put together as directions on cake mix tell you.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) round pans.
Set aside to cool.

title: super bowl sunday cake 'n' frosting
directions: One combines the pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl. Next, beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of an electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Then, fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes about 4 cups or enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.
Frosted cake should be refrigerated, so this type frosting will stay firm.
For a firmer frosting, one can let this mixture stand 5 minutes before folding in the Cool Whip.

title: butter biscuits
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients, then add milk.
Stir with fork until dough forms into a ball.
Knead gently 6 times.

title: fluffy chocolate cream pie
directions: *Graham cracker crust may be substituted.

title: scandinavian apple cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar and butter in bowl.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to apple mixture.
Stir only until blended.
Divide batter between 2 greased 8 or 9-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Wrap well and refrigerate.
The longer you let it stand, the better it is.

title: orange filling
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown in skillet with the oleo.
Remove chicken to a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
In the drippings, saute onions and celery (tender).
Add cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste ever so often (3 times).
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brazilian brigadeiro
directions: Mix together in a pan:
condensed milk, butter and Nestle Quik. Stir with wooden spoon continuously over medium heat.
When the mixture begins to pull away from the pan, the Brigadeiro is ready.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roast 3 to 4 pound beef roast until done.
Slice and add to sauce.
Simmer.
Serve on buns.

title: ernest tea
directions: Steep the tea, mint and lemon rind in the boiling water for 12 minutes.
Remove the tea, mint and lemon rind from the water.
Add the lemon juice and sugar and strain.
Add the cold water.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach supreme quiche
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: "peach tree ribs"
directions: Boil ribs; drain.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients for marinade; pour over ribs and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Drain well; reserve the marinade for basting. Grill ribs and baste.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple and lemon juice in enough orange juice to make 1 cup.
Add sweetener. Dissolve cornstarch in water. Add to juices.
Boil, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cool.
Mix all together.
Add sliced bananas, apples, grapes, etc.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (cake will not test done).
Cook cake for 10 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together very thoroughly with your hands for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover bowl and set overnight in refrigerator.
Form into logs 8 x 2-inch or 6 logs per 5 pounds ground beef.
Bake in oven for 3 hours at 200° turning every 45 minutes.
Use broiler pan to bake on to let grease drip.
As soon as log is done, wrap in paper towels to soak up all excess grease. Serve when cool.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.
Can be frozen.

title: favorite punch
directions: Mix juices and water.
Pour over ice and add giner ale when serving.
Yield: 40 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in a greased pan.
Makes 2 or 3 loaves.
Bake at 350°.

title: ethel's creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine filling ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from the edge comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream and nuts. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: play dough
directions: In heavy aluminum saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes, or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
May add a few drops of oil of wintergreen, cloves or cinnamon to give a more pleasant aroma. Knead slightly almost immediately.
Store in a plastic bag in an airtight container.
Will keep several weeks.
Has a pleasing texture.

title: meat potato quiche
directions: Place potatoes in oil in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake potatoes for 15 minutes at 400°.
Brown and drain sausage.
Layer cheese, onion, sausage and green pepper over potatoes.
Beat milk and eggs; pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: spicy cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly in medium bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Nice with ham.

title: microwave sweet crispix mix
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes, without stirring.
Pour Crispix, pretzels and peanuts in turkey pan.
Pour boiling mixture over top.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Boil chicken in 2 quarts water with 2 teaspoons salt added. Cook until tender.
Put tomatoes, corn and corn meal, which has been moistened with the milk, into chicken broth, which has boiled down to 1 or 1 1/2 quarts liquid.
Boil, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and olives and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Turn low so corn meal won't scorch and stir frequently.
Put chicken and olives in a minute or two before removing from heat.
Pour into "Pammed" or oiled covered casserole and bake slowly for 1 hour at 300°.
Don't cut chicken pieces too small.
Olives may be placed on top of mixture after it is poured into casserole.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Drain pineapple.
Whip cream.
Add all ingredients together; mix.
Put in refrigerator.
May be in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, then fry in hot butter.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry onion and rice in oil until golden.
Fry eggs until firm. Cut into squares.
Add eggs, meat, soy sauce, vegetables, salt and pepper to rice.
Fry for a few minutes and serve.

title: melt-in-your-mouth-meat balls
directions: Soak bread in cold water. Squeeze out water. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Form into balls of desired size. Place meat balls on Teflon-coated or lightly greased baking dishes. Brown in oven at 400° for about 15 minutes. Drain and freeze or simmer in spaghetti sauce. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano; mix well.
Add beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Place half of spaghetti in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with half of sauce and sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup and water until smooth.
Pour over spaghetti mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple pie 21st century
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Remove crusts from bread slices.
Cut bread slices into 4 strips each.
Set aside.
Measure spices, sugar, melted margarine and egg together. Set aside. Peel apples, slice and place evenly on bottom of sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour or spread spices, etc., on top of apples as evenly as possible.
Place bread strips evenly on top of filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until apples can be pierced with a fork.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes.
Peel potatoes and beat.
Add butter and margarine to hot potatoes and beat.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, 2 or 3 at a time.
Add milk and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Makes 5 to 6 pies.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Don't overcook.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugars, eggs, vanilla and water.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meatballs and cheesy shells
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs (moistened with milk), egg, cheese, parsley, garlic and peppers.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in oil and cook until done.
Meanwhile, heat tomato sauce and oregano.
Keep warm.
Cook shells and drain.
Spoon a thin coating of sauce in oiled baking dish.
Fill each shell with Ricotta cheese and place in dish along with meatballs.
Spoon remaining sauce over contents in baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until heated.
Serves 4.

title: super sandwich
directions: In a bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, onion, olives, and salad dressing; set aside. Cut 1 inch off the top of bread, leaving a 1/2 inch shell. Layer a 1/4 of the ham, salami, pork and cheeses inside the shell. Top with 1/3 of the vegetable mixture. Repeat layers, ending with meat and cheeses, gently pressing down to flatten as needed. Replace bread top; wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Steep tea bags 5 minutes in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, sauces, onions and small handful of chipped beef. Form into a ball and roll in remaining chipped beef. Chill. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: craig's energy snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Great for lunch boxes, quick snacks, trips in the car, or just to watch TV.
Kids love to make it!

title: marmalade chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash the chicken and pat dry.
Place in a baking pan in a single layer.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour the sauce over the chicken.
Bake chicken, covered, with aluminum foil at 350°
for 50 minutes. Uncover the chicken, spoon the sauce over the top of the chicken and continue to bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
If there is extra sauce, it can be refrigerated for a few weeks.

title: egg beaters
directions: Mix together and cook.

title: dark fudge
directions: Cook sugar, chocolate, butter and milk, stirring constantly, until mixture forms soft ball (234°).
Cool slightly and add marshmallows and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Add 1 cup nuts, if desired.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Season each pork chop with salt, pepper and garlic.
Dip into flour.
Brown in canola oil about 10 minutes, browning onion at the same time in the same skillet.
Drain.
Stir in soup and water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer until pork chops are fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Drain pineapple and peaches well; reserving juices.
Add milk to juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Add pudding mix to liquid and shake well.
In bowl, add well drained canned fruit and all of the ingredients, including pudding mixture.
Stir in Cool Whip and garnish as you wish.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar and water at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into boiling syrup.

title: cranberry-banana pie
directions: Grind cranberries.
Combine with banana and 1/2 c. sugar.
Set aside.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs with 6 Tbsp. butter, melted. Press 1/2 crumbs in bottom of 9-inch pie dish.
Cream 1/2 c. butter and 1 c. sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Fold in nuts.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Top with cranberry mixture. Whip cream and spread over cranberries.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: pot roast in beer
directions: Dissolve beef cubes in water.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil and add meat.
Lower heat and simmer 3 hours.
After about 2 hours add carrots, onions and potatoes.
When cooked, remove to platter.
Strain juice and make gravy.

title: baked french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel each potato and cut lengthwise and quarter.
Slice into thin slices the size of matchsticks.
Coat a baking sheet sprayed 3 times with vegetable oil.
Combine the egg whites and spice in a bowl.
Add the potato fries and cover well with the egg whites.
Place the coated fries on baking sheet. Spread them in single layer, leaving space between. Insert baking sheet on bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. As they brown, turn fries with spatula so they brown evenly.
Serve while still hot.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; fry into patties.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix; put in dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soften yeast in water (110°).
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: pineapple macaroons
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine drained pineapple with Eagle Brand, coconut, nuts, butter, lemon peel and almond extract. Combine flour and baking powder.
Beat into pineapple mixture until blended.
Spoon by heaping tablespoonfuls 1-inch apart onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onions; cook a few minutes more.
Add flour.
Dump into big soup kettle.
Add everything else, except macaroni.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Cook macaroni separately; add last.
A little red wine added just before serving is very good. Makes 3 gallons or 48 (1-cup) servings.

title: "death to dieters" chicken lasagna(if i ever get to san francisco!!!)
directions: Cook chicken and slice.
Cook noodles.
Saute mushrooms and onion.
Make Hollandaise sauce.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, vegetable oil and mandarin oranges.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spicy roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Quarter potatoes and place in large roasting
pan.
Combine other ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes and toss with 2 spoons.
Bake, stirring occasionally, until potatoes
are tender browned (40 to 60 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: no bake chocolate cheese cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add other ingredients except whipped heavy cream.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add whipped cream to chocolate mixture and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: spinach sauté over brown rice
directions: Saut onion and squash in olive oil, then add a clove or two of chopped garlic. Add spinach leaves and stir until the leaves wilt. Just adjust the amounts to however much you want or need. Serve over brown rice cooked in chicken broth with spices added such as thyme, oregano, garlic, etc. to your taste. Serves about 4, using a bunch of spinach. Not sure if you can freeze; probably. Can make ahead.

title: poke salad
directions: Pick it, wash it, parboil it, wash again and cook until tender.
Drain; squeeze water out.
Cook in oil for 30 minutes. Add 4 eggs; stir together until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all together.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato pie
directions: In an unbaked pie crust, add mixed ingredients.
Add top crust. Have small cuts to vent the steam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with hot milk (not boiled) with a little butter, salt and pepper. Cut a piece of pie; put in a bowl.
Add as much warm milk as you like.
Enjoy.

title: pine nut, rice and feta salad
directions: Stir together 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir together oil, vinegar and pepper.
Add to rice mixture, tossing to coat.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: ship wreck
directions: Heat soup and water in pan and pour on top of casserole. Place foil on top of dish while cooking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious cornbread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, oil and sugar together. Then combine milk and eggs.
Bake in a greased pan at about 350°.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: You put a layer of macaroni, then a layer of cheese, sliced, then another layer of macaroni and another layer of cheese. Beat your eggs and milk together and cover.
Slice the margarine in thin slices. Cover well with the margarine. Bake in oven at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: *If you want more of a meat flavor, add 2 pounds.
You can also add more vegetables, if you like.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar.
Pat in bottom of 9x13 pan. Bake 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pita pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread pizza sauce over pita bread. Add fresh vegetables; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake on top rack of oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and pita is crisp.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Beat eggs.
Dip slices in egg and then bread crumbs.
Saute eggplant in olive oil until golden brown.
Use a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer eggplant one slice thick on bottom.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and basil. Cover with Mozzarella and tomato sauce.
Alternate layers finishing with sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until bubbling.

title: bob and ken's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Cook at 350°.
Drain off any excess grease.

title: kumquats (preserved-whole)
directions: Mix sugar and water together and boil for 5 minutes to make syrup.
Cool.
Wash kumquats thoroughly.
Cut small cross in blossom end with scissors.
Place in cooled syrup.
Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer.
Cover and simmer gently for 1 hour.
Do not remove cover until fruit and syrup are cool.
Fruit will stay plump.
(If you remove cover before both are cool, the fruit will wrinkle.)
Put in jars and keep refrigerated.

title: lime (buttermilk) jello
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and add lime Jell-O and chilled buttermilk.
Chill, then add Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: pulled molasses candy
directions: Boil molasses, water and sugar briskly until it brittles when tested in water.
Pour in dripping pan when cool enough to handle. Pull, flavor and cut in pieces.

title: oreng popcickle
directions: Pore oreng juice into the ice tray.
Then put foil on the ice tray.
Push the clean popcickle sticks were the oreng juice is. Set the ice tray in the freezer for 3 hours.
Take them out and eat them!

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in square baking dish.
Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Pour over melted butter.
Add fruit. Bake for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly by hand.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie tray.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: rich chocolate icing
directions: In saucepan, stir the sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When it boils, reduce heat to medium-low.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until mixture starts to thicken.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over cake.

title: new orleans okra
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer okra, tomatoes, salt, pepper, onion and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover until time to brown.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Melt margarine in pan, add sugar.
Let cool.
Add flour, butterscotch bits, chocolate bits and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cut while hot.

title: double crust coconut pie
directions: Thaw coconut.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, coconut, salt and cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into coconut mixture. Spoon into prepared pie plate and cover with top crust.
Brush lightly with milk or cream.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using the two cups of milk.
Mix this with Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of graham cracker squares.
Place 1/2 of pudding mixture on crackers.
Top with a second layer of crackers and remainder of pudding mix.
Top with third layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Chill several hours and cut in squares.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: 1st:
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add potatoes, 2 cups water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in corn, ham and milk.
Blend flour with 1/2 cup water; stir into chowder.
Cook until thickens. Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 6 cups.

title: lucy's peanut brittle(from the files of lucy crutchfield)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and cook together until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Then add peanuts and butter and cook in the syrup until slightly browned.
Add vanilla; remove mixture from heat and add soda.
Mix well and pour into buttered pans, spreading thinly.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Grease and flour pan or spray with Pam.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Alternate milk and flour and vanilla.
Bake until done.

title: sweet rolls(cinnamon rolls)
directions: Scald 2/3 cup of milk.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, the salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 2/3 cup lukewarm water and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add to milk mixture.
Add the eggs and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add 3 more cups flour; knead. Place in greased bowl; brush lightly with shortening.
Let double in bulk.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll into oblong 14 x 8 x 1/4-inch.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut slices 1-inch thick. Place, cut side up, about 1 inch apart in greased shallow pan.
Let double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: chicken 'n dressing bake
directions: Toss cooked stuffing with 1/2 can of soup, the broth and eggs. Spread in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch greased baking dish; top with chicken.
Combine remaining soup with milk and pimento; pour over all.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.

title: my favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add 1/2 cup milk to well beaten egg yolks, then blend into dry ingredients.
Stir until all lumps are dissolved.
Add remaining milk and mix.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then cook over low heat until desired thickness.
Add vanilla and butter.
Stir and set aside until crust is ready.
Pour into slightly baked crust.
Top with meringue.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: grape lemonade punch
directions: Remove seeds from lemon and orange juices, but do not strain. Blend in the sugar until thoroughly dissolved.
Add the chilled grape juice and ice water.
Place 2 tablespoons of crushed ice into five 8 ounce glasses.
Fill with lemonade.
Garnish with a lemon slice.
Add a sprig of mint.
Serves 5.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Grease dish and place rice in bottom.
Combine soup and water and pour half of mixture over rice.
Place chicken over rice.
Add salt and pepper and remaining soup.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add chili powder, soup and tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken to sauce, broken up.

title: quick potato salad
directions: When cool enough to handle, cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes. In large bowl, combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing; toss gently.
Dust top with paprika.
Garnish with chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown chicken with butter or margarine on both sides in skillet.
In a medium size bowl, combine and whisk together chicken mushroom soup and heavy cream.
Set aside.
Add wine to chicken and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soup and cream mixture to skillet, pouring over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Serve over Rice Pilaf.
Enjoy.

title: mennonite borscht
directions: All ingredients are approximate.
Cook meat until tender; bone and cut up.
Add to soup stock with remainder of ingredients, except cream.
Simmer until done.
Add cream and serve.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Slice dinner size rolls (tray) in half.
Combine margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread mixture on one-half of roll and put ham and cheese on the other half.
Put together.
Cover with foil and warm in oven.

title: low-fat, low-sodium thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with salad or use on sandwiches.

title: cranberry dessert (or salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 8 x 2-inch pan and freeze.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Layer filling with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken fried spam
directions: Cut the meat into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Mix the eggs and milk together.
Dip into the flour; repeat once. Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: no fuss lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown meat. Add Ragu, tomatoes, seasoning and salt. Mix well. Cook together until hot. In small bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese (set aside).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms, chop finely and set aside.
In skillet, melt butter, add stems and cook until tender.
Add onion soup mix, bread crumbs and almonds; mix well.
Stir in sherry.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar with a fork.
Don't use mixer at all. Beat in egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate with milk and flour. Add fruit.
Mix lightly.
Have a 12 x 6-inch baking pan greased with butter and pour batter.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, water, pepper and red pepper and set aside.
Stir-fry garlic, frozen pea pods, red pepper and mushrooms until tender; set aside.
In 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry round steak and add mixture until thick.
Add vegetables.
Serve over noodles.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, nuts. Stir in milk. Mix well, add extract and mix. Let set until dry to the touch. Shape into balls. Melt chocolate and wax. Dip balls into chocolate. Put on wax paper to let dry.

title: cabbage supreme
directions: You will also need 1 glass dish, 13 x 13.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: Select a round platter.
Spread beans (straight from can) over platter.
Pour green chilies over beans evenly.
Cut olives in slices and spread over chilies.
Whip up sour cream before spooning it out and smoothing it over the olives with a fork.
Next, de-pit avocados and scrape out the inside into another bowl.
Using a fork will make avocados creamy enough to spread over sour cream.
(May be difficult but continue.)
Dice tomatoes and spread over avocados.
Shred the cheese over tomatoes and serve.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake uncovered 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
This can be made the night before.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs together.
Add any ingredients you wish such as chocolate chips or add oatmeal or coconut or any kind of fruit and nuts.

title: honey-paprika sweet onions
directions: Place onions, cut side up, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients; pour over onions.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Mix wild rice, salt and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer on low for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until done.
Add sauted mixture to salt, pepper, flour and milk and heat. Add wild rice, heat again.
Serve with chopped parsley and/or bacon, crumbled.

title: peaches and cream cheese cobbler
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Place peaches or pineapple around batter.

title: chocolate date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dates and chocolate.
Blend together well.
Stir in coffee, soda, eggs and vegetable oil.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix all together, then add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Make golfball sized cookies and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies!

title: apple cranberry salad
directions: Boil water; pour in package of jello.
Melt cream cheese in jello while hot.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Top with 1 cup of grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: basic yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk; add margarine, sugar and salt.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add to the cooled milk mixture.
Add beaten eggs and 2 cups of the flour (which may be whole wheat) and beat with mixer.
Add remaining flour gradually, stirring by hand to get the feel of the stiffness of the dough.
When stiff, turn onto a board that has been floured and knead until it loses its stickiness. Turn into a large greased bowl or kettle and turn so exposed top has grease covering.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk; punch down, let rest a few minutes and form according to the desired use.
If a coffee cake or sweet roll is desired, more butter may be rolled into the dough as you fold the dough and roll.
One third of dough will give you a dozen large dinner rolls or a larger coffee ring.

title: camp cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients; seal in plastic bag.
Measure 3 to 4 tablespoons cocoa mixture into mug; add boiling water.
Stir until cocoa mixture is dissolved.
Makes about 7 cups of dry cocoa mixture.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slightly thaw potatoes; add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 3-quart baking casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle oleo over top of cornflakes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: southern baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
With pastry blender or two knives, work shortening into flour until it looks like coarse cornmeal.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Pour in half of milk.
Mix thoroughly and lightly with a fork.
Add more milk and mix until dough clings to fork and forms a ball.
(Stir as little as possible for a light dough.)
Turn dough onto a floured surface and roll with floured rolling pin or pat with floured hands to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into circles with floured biscuit cutter or small size glass.
Place on greased pans, sides lightly touching.
Bake in 450° oven about 15 to 18 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve very hot with butter and honey or jam.
Makes 18 to 20 biscuits about 2 inches in diameter.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Mix together and pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: never fail buns
directions: Mix in saucepan the milk, shortening and sugar; heat to scalding point.
Cool.
Combine with the dissolved yeast, beaten eggs and salt, then mix in 2 cups of the flour.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Add in remaining 4 1/2 cups flour.
Mix and knead well. Let rise, punch down and make into buns.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients directly in casserole.
Let stand overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Cook hamburger with chopped onion.
Add spices.
Cook rice; let cool some.
In a big pan, mix soups and salsa; heat on top of stove until it starts to bubble, then add drained hamburger and rice.
Stir together; let simmer while you grate the cheese. Crush chips and add to mixture.
Smooth top.
Sprinkle with both kinds of cheese.
Put lid on top.
Turn off heat and let set for a few minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with salt water; soak 1/2 hour. Dry.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Dip eggplant slices in egg mixture.
Fry both sides quickly; drain on paper towels.
Arrange in layers: eggplant, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan, in that order.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a
pie
plate
casserole
or spring-form pan, spread bean dip.
Mash	avocados with lemon juice and salt and spread half on bean mixture.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning
and
spread over avocado mixture.
Next, layer in remaining half
of avocados, the vegetables in order listed and the cheese.
Chill	for
several hours.
Serve with traditional flavor Tostitos.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and serve warm.

title: sour pickles
directions: Pack clean jars with cucumbers.
Fill with 2/3 vinegar, 1/3 water and 2 grains saccharin.
Put in hot water bath until cucumbers turn a pickle color.
Remove from water immediately.

title: zippy chicken ziti
directions: Prepare ziti according to package directions; add broccoli during last minute of cooking. Drain; add garlic, alfredo sauce, chicken, tomatoes and cheese, mixing well. Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13 casserole; set aside. Toss bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over ziti. Bake at 350° until top is golden, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bubble pipe liquid
directions: Mix soap powder and water and store in bottles for future use.

title: seven layer munch
directions: Mix melted margarine with graham cracker crumbs and press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut over bottom.
Then chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate full of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bacon 'n eggs pancake roll-up
directions: Prepare pancakes using pancake mix.
Cut 8 slices bacon into pieces 1
inch
long.
Pan-fry
until
lightly
browned. Drain. Cook 8 additional bacon slices; drain and keep warm.

title: blue hake del mar
directions: *Or can use any deboned whitefish equal to 1 pound of fillets (i.e., perch).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: empanaditas
directions: Cook beef, pepper and onion in heavy skillet; do not brown. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 25 minutes. Remove from heat. Serve in empanadita dough.

title: rice muffins
directions: Mix rice, milk, oil and beaten eggs together well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into batter.
Mix until flour is dampened.
Do not beat!
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add milk to asparagus liquid to equal one can of milk.

title: never fail dumplings for stew
directions: Sift flour,
baking
powder
and
salt; add parsley and thyme. With pastry blender, cut in shortening until like very coarse corn meal.	With fork, lightly mix in milk to form soft dough. Stir as little as possible.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls into boiling
stew.
Simmer
for
10 minutes, uncovered, then cover and simmer an additional 10 minutes.

title: goldie's chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda and put aside.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large bowl.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Add flour, then nuts and chips (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie tins 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 435°.
Sift first 4 ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Add cornmeal.
Combine 1/4 cup oil, brown sugar and eggs. Add buttermilk to this and then combine with dry ingredients. Beat only until smooth.
Cover bottom of 10-inch cast-iron skillet with bacon drippings.
Heat on top of stove until very hot.
Pour batter in skillet.
Immediately put in oven.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from skillet so that crust is on top.
(This is good to use in any cornbread dressing.)

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper. Saute the onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix together with other ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking casserole dish.
Top with the Ritz crackers and pour the melted oleo over the entire dish.
Bake until bubbly and top is brown at 375° or until firm.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Pour off fat.
In large skillet, combine kidney beans, tomatoes, water, onion, bay leaf, salt, garlic salt, thyme and pepper.
Add sausage.
Simmer covered 1 hour.
Add potatoes and green pepper.
Cook covered 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaves and serve.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: christmas trees or sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
