Add unbeaten egg, sifted dry ingredients, flavoring and a few drops of vegetable coloring.
Mix well.

title: tortilla-black bean casserole
directions: In large skillet, combine onion, green pepper, undrained tomatoes, picante sauce, garlic and cumin.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat until well mixed.
Mix milk with water mixture.
Mix salt with flour.
Alternate, adding these and mix
thoroughly.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven or until a straw comes out clean when placed in center.
Use loaf tin (greased).
Makes one large loaf.

title: great dump cake
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ingredients in order and do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more, until cake is firm to touch.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Mix well and put in buttered pan.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: sloppy joes in crock-pot
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; pour into a colander and rinse well.
Put into crock-pot; add onions, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Stir thoroughly; salt to taste.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours; high 4 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour in loaf pan at 325°.
Freezes well.
Slice thin when cold.

title: pierogi(cheese filled dumplings)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a large bowl; make a well.
Add 2 beaten eggs and water; stir to make a soft dough. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until quite elastic.
Cover with bowl and allow to rest 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizers
directions: Take mushrooms and wash; cut off stems and dice stems in fry-pan with sausage, garlic and seasoning.
When completely cooked, remove from heat; add salsa, bread crumbs and cheese and mix.
Lay mushroom caps on flat surface and fill with sausage mixture.
Place stuffed mushrooms on an oiled baking pan.
Add a little water to the pan and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: hershey's more chips chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually beat into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes about 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Thaw strawberries. Combine orange juice, lemonade and water. Add strawberries and ginger ale when ready to serve.
Pour over ice cubes. Garnish with fresh strawberries and orange slices. Yields 2 quarts.

title: swiss holiday bread
directions: Sprinkle the yeast into 2 1/4 cups warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Scald the milk and pour into large bowl.
Stir in the sugar, butter and salt and let sit until lukewarm.
Beat in 2 cups of flour, then the yeast, egg and enough extra flour to make a soft dough (1 1/2 to 1 3/4 cups).
Turn the dough out on a lightly floured surface.
Cover with a towel and let it stand for 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in a lightly greased bowl, turning it once to grease the whole surface.
Cover and leave to rise in a warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch the dough and let it rise again until it doubles in size.
Punch it down and using hands, work in the citron, raisins, almonds, cherries and lemon rind.
Divide the dough in half; shape into two loaves and put into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Let rise until almost doubled in bulk, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Brush the loaves with the beaten egg, then bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until they sound hollow when tapped with the finger.
Remove the loaves from the pans and cool on a rack.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Heat first 3 ingredients in large casserole dish for 5 minutes.
Add soup and heat until bubbly.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown turkey and pork meat in pan.
Drain juice off and add tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer meat for 30 minutes. Put lasagna noodles on to boil at this time.
While noodles are boiling, grated the Mozzarella cheese and open Ricotta.
When noodles are tender, place small amount of meat juice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Start layering ingredients: noodles, meat and sauce, Mozzarella and Ricotta.
The next layer of noodles should be placed in the opposite direction.
Continue layering pattern stopping with Ricotta on top.

title: shrimp roll
directions: Combine all but walnuts; blend and roll into ball.
Roll into chopped walnuts.
Wrap in Glad Wrap and chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together, adding melted butter last.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Meringue.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly and add sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir until well mixed. Spread pecans on bottom of 9-inch pie shell; cover with filling. Place in oven and reduce oven temperature down to 350°. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, until filling is firm in the middle.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toast bread slices lightly.
Break bread into small pieces in casserole. Sprinkle with raisins.
Blend eggs, brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually stir in milk; pour over bread in casserole.
Place casserole in pan of very hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oyster asparagus soup
directions: Simmer oysters and liquid in skillet for 1 minute until edges of oysters curl.
Remove oysters and chop.
Add margarine to oyster liquid and heat.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
When milk begins to simmer, add chopped oysters, artichokes, asparagus, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beer batter(for onion rings, shrimp, etc.)
directions: Combine flour and beer.
Blend with whisk.
Cover bowl and allow to sit at room temperature overnight.
Make very light crispy batter.

title: uncle harold's secret recipe hot potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes, macaroni and onion until tender.
When done, drain off 1/2 of remaining water.
Add to this the remaining spices.
All spice amounts can be adjusted to taste.
Serve on cold winter days with a very large pitcher of ice tea.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Cut several cherry halves to place on top of salad.
Put into dish and freeze.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time. Add vanilla and sour cream.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until well mixed.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.
Bake in tube pan.

title: red snapper with roasted pecans
directions: In a motor, grind pepper, salt, paprika and fennel seed. Sprinkle over each filet.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large frying pan.
Add fish and cook 4 minutes.
Turn over filets and cook 4 minutes.
Remove cooked filets from pan.
Add remaining butter to pan and melt.
Add pecans.
Cook 1 minute.
Add lemon juice and mix.
Pan over cooked hot filets.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut round steak into 1-inch cubes and fry in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer partially covered for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake #3
directions: Place 15 halved graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture on top of graham crackers, then place 15 more halved graham crackers on top.
Pour the rest of the pudding mixture on top; place 15 more crackers on top.
Mix 5 or 6 tablespoons of boiling water with frosting mix; smooth frosting on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl with fork until crumbly. Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased rectangular pan, 13x9x2-inch.
Bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes, at 350 degrees. Favorite cheesecake recipe:
Use pastry blender to mix crust; much easier.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put eggs in quart jar with peppers.
In 2-quart pan, heat remaining ingredients until you can't hold your finger in it. Pour over eggs, making sure to cover all eggs.
Seal and let stand 1 to 2 weeks.
Store in refrigerator after opening.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap apples in rolls and place in baking dish.
Mix melted butter, sugar and water.
Pour over apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash cooked potato.
Slowly begin adding sugar while stirring, until mixture has become a ball of dough.
Roll out thin. Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.

title: romance cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients. Spread on ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Bake 10 minutes

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal in boiling water and let stand 20 minutes.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in flat pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for around 45 to 50 minutes.

title: i scream muffins
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add the egg, ice cream and oil. Stir just until moistened.

title: president clinton's favorite pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan; cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternating with buttermilk.
Bake 1 hour 25 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Dough will be sticky.
Knead in enough flour to handle, but don't make dough stiff.
Roll and cut.
Let rise 30 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 400° 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough will last a week in the refrigerator, but will need to rise at least a full hour once cut.

title: english toffee
directions: Beat the margarine and sugar for 5 minutes or longer, until fluffy and creamy.
Add the vanilla, cooled chocolate and 2 eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add 2 more eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add 2 more eggs and the dry milk crystals; beat 2 minutes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with graham cracker crust.
Chill or freeze overnight.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all in a heavy boiler.
Bring to a full boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into large bowl and beat until right to spread.
Seems to cook in 2 1/2 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, in a greased casserole dish (top will brown) about 35 minutes.
This dish can be doubled or tripled.
(Just increase stuffing by 1/2 cup each time.)

title: pink salmon salad
directions: Finely chop celery, onions, peppers and eggs.
Use a fork to flake the salmon.
Add ingredients to 2 cups cooked and drained macaroni shells.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise (Hellmann's).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients in pot.
Simmer until rice is cooked.
Great one pot meal!!

title: quickie but good dip
directions: Melt jalapeno cheese with can of chili in a double boiler. Serve in a chafing dish as dip with Fritos on side.

title: sundae cake
directions: Make German chocolate cake. Cool completely. Make holes on top of the cake with a toothpick. Pour Eagle Brand milk slowly over the cake; let it soak in. Warm the jar of Hershey's hot fudge in the microwave oven just enough to pour easily. Spread the hot fudge over the top of the cake. Cool completely. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.
Crush the Heath bars and sprinkle over the Cool Whip. Refrigerate. This keeps well for several days, gets better each day.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats, set aside.
Mix next 7 ingredients. Add oat mixture, flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Top with 1 cup crushed saltine cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well, chill and serve.

title: belle tippett's scalloped eggplant
directions: Wash, but do not peel green tomatoes.
Drain.
Slice crosswise in about 1/2-inch slices or smaller.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll in mixture of cornmeal and flour.
Fry in hot shortening, turning when brown.

title: southern strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and 3/4 sugar together into bowl and cut in shortening.
Combine the milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well, knead on a floured surface, then put into a 10-inch round cake pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes (until light brown top).
Remove from pan and split.
Butter while hot.
Mash the strawberries and stir in remaining sugar.
Place half the strawberries between layers of shortcake and place remaining strawberries on top.
Serve with home-whipped cream. Yum! Yum!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon whipper snappers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Make paste with flour and milk.
Add to other ingredients.
Add bread crumbs to make patty consistency.
Coat patty with bread crumbs and brown in oil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together except 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Pour into baking dish, sprinkle with remaining cup of cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil, milk, orange juice and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder and pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° to 375° oven.

title: moma kemps banana bread
directions: Soften butter, mix flour and sugar in a large bowl. Beat eggs and add to butter. Add all ingredients in large bowl, mix well, then add nuts. Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until done.

title: lazy morning breakfast casserole
directions: Layer croutons in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish; add grated cheese and sausage.
Mix eggs and 2 1/2 cups milk; pour over layers and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened; beat in sugar.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold
in coconut and whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Let stand at room temperature to soften before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put pork chops in bottom of large pot or crock-pot.
Layer vegetables on top of chops.
Cook on low until done.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Mixture will be stiff.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain thoroughly.
Cube cheese.
Combine sausage and cheese in a microwave bowl.
Place in microwave for 3 minutes on High; stir and repeat until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread and place under broiler until slightly browned.
This also makes a great dip for corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: 9 layer mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning per package directions.
Spread meat in bottom of 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Layer beans, then sour cream, then cheese.
Garnish with diced tomatoes, scallions and olives.
Bake in 350° oven until hot; remove.
Add lettuce, if desired.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: cheesy broccoli casserolefort collins, colorado
directions: Steam broccoli until it separates.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix warm broccoli and rice with remaining ingredients.
Put in greased 2 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Casserole may be mixed the day before serving and refrigerated until ready to use.
Makes 5 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add macaroni, peas, tomato soup and salt to taste.
Pour into a baking dish. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter until well blended.
Melt butter in an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: judi's pineapple-raisin kugel
directions: Boil noodles and set aside.
Mix beaten eggs, cottage cheese, vanilla, sour cream, margarine and sugar together.
Pour noodles into egg mixture.
Add pineapple chunks and raisins.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and crumble cornflakes.
Add pats of margarine to the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (may need an additional 20 minutes to bake).

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan. Boil to 232° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla flavoring. Stir until fudge loses shininess and is thick. Pour into small buttered pan. Allow to cool.

title: tasty breakfast egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch iron skillet or deep pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple, walnut halves and cherries over brown sugar.
Sprinkle chopped nuts around outer edges; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add sifted flour with baking powder and salt.
Add water; beat thoroughly.
Pour over fruit and nuts in skillet.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) about 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruity orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add pecans, milk and pineapple. Refrigerate until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with chopped onion until tender; drain and cool. Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a pan and put dressing in margarine; brown slightly.
Reserve 1/4 of the dressing mixture.
Add remaining dressing to squash, sour cream, carrot and salt and pepper to taste; mix well.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread out on large plate.
Top with ice cream topping.
Top with pecans.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice and Jell-O.
Simmer until dissolved. Let it cool.
While cooling, mash cottage cheese with a fork. Fold in Cool Whip and cottage cheese into pineapple mixture. Refrigerate.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese (best done in a crock-pot).
Mix beef, cheese and Ro-Tel sauce or jalapeno relish.
Serve warm with nachos or corn chips

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix together tuna, cream cheese, Tabasco sauce, onion, salt, 4 tablespoons parsley flakes and roll into a ball or log.
On wax paper mix 2 tablespoons parsley flakes and chopped nuts.
Roll tuna in mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sinful pan-fried catfish
directions: Wash catfish and if inside skin has dark areas, cut off. Sprinkle fish with generous amount of lemon juice.
Salt and pepper and set aside.
Mix remaining salt, pepper, cornmeal and flour. Pour enough oil for about 3-inches in bottom of 3-quart saucepan. Roll catfish in cornmeal mixture and drop into hot fat.
Brown and drain on paper towels.
Extra cornmeal mixture may be needed.
If fish are too large, cut in half.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, soup, milk and onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat all these together until well blended. Then add self-rising flour, one cup at a time, until a stiff dough forms. This will take 4 or 5 cups flour. Pour dough onto floured wax paper. Make into biscuits or roll dough out and cut into shapes. Bake at 375° until done. It usually takes 12 to 15 minutes.

title: andy's deep fried turkey
directions: Season the turkey as you would season a roast.
With remaining seasoning, rub over outside of bird.
Place whole turkey into pot of oil with a temperature of 250 to 270° (it takes about 30 minutes to get oil at proper temperature).
You can use the onion as a temperature gauge when frying, the onion skin will start to burn before the turkey.
At the proper temperature your oil will have a slow, rolling boil.

title: sunday stew(portuguese)
directions: Peel and chop onions. Cut celery into small cubes.
Brown meat in a pot while stirring so that it evenly crumbles.
Saute onion and celery with meat.
When meat is almost brown, season and add bouillon cube, tomato paste and water; stir well and simmer for several minutes. Prepare pasta according to directions on package. Add cooked pasta to stew.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Cooking time:
20 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, mix soup and reserved broth. Bring to a boil and pour over chicken.
In another bowl, mix melted margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. (I never cook anything that high.)
I prefer to add a can of Veg-All vegetables over the chicken.
You can also add hard-boiled eggs or other vegetables of choice.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let congeal.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Place cookies in a large zip-lock freezer bag and use a can to crush them into crumbs to look like dirt.
Be careful not to punch a hole in the bag.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, margarine, and powdered sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, combine instant pudding and milk.
Blend well.
Then, fold this into the cream cheese mixture.
Next, fold in the cool whip. In a 9 x13 inch pan, sprinkle a thin layer of cookie crumbs. Top with a layer of the pudding mixture.
Sprinkle another thin layer of crumbs, then the rest of the pudding.
The final layer of crumbs should cover the dessert well, resembling dirt.
As a finishing touch, add some "gummy" worms to the top, pushing the ends into the surface.
"Plant" small flowers near one corner.

title: blueberry streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl, combine blueberries, Eagle Brand and lemon peel.

title: appetizer shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing until very smooth. Add onions and garlic salt.
Mix in drained tiny shrimp.
Chill and serve with your choice of crackers or sliced party bread.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and pecans. Slowly add flour; mix well. Add vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Scald milk; add 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves and shortening melts.
Cool liquid to lukewarm.
Combine water, yeast and 3 tablespoons sugar in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in milk mixture, eggs and 3 cups of flour; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring until a soft dough is formed.
Turn dough out on floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
Proceed to make cinnamon rolls or other sweet rolls.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour half into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Spoon sour cream over firm Jell-O mixture. Spoon remaining Jell-O mixture over this and refrigerate until firm.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix all together and add milk if needed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Boil together:
1 cup vinegar, 2 cups sugar, 1 tbsp salt, 1 tbsp mustard seed, 1 tbsp celery seed and 1/3 tsp turmeric.

title: chicken and pineapple salad
directions: Combine chicken, pecans, green pepper, celery and pineapple in bowl; toss to mix.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill overnight. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Soften the butter.
In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and beat with a mixer until everything is mixed good, then spoon drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 min.

title: volcano cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour 2 cups into a greased 9-inch round pan and 2 cups into a greased 8-inch round pan and remaining batter in a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 350°; layers for 18 to 22 minutes or until done and the bowl 35 to 40 minutes or until done. Cool completely.

title: tuna ring
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread onto biscuit mix that has been rolled out (use 2 cups biscuit mix with 1/2 cup water).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hearty slovak stew
directions: In Dutch
oven	or
large
pot, melt butter; add onion, potatoes, apple
and
garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir in sauerkraut, tomatoes, broth, sausage, caraway seed and pepper.
Cover
and
simmer
minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 hearty servings!

title: fruit punch
directions: Thaw frozen concentrates, then add to pineapple juice.
Pour into empty milk carton and freeze.
Take from freezer 3 hours or less before using; add 1/2 gallon ginger ale just before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or longer.
Use 3 cake pans.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Divide in half and put one half in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish or large glass bowl.
Chill until firm.
To remaining half, add 2 tablespoons sour cream and whip.
Pour on top of firm jello.
Chill.
Repeat with 4 remaining flavors, remembering to chill between each layer.

title: mary's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand while mixing the rest of the cake.
Cream together sugar, brown sugar and butter. Add egg and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to butter mixture.
Add oatmeal mixture and vanilla. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in casserole and cover with 1/2 can soup and milk.
After 1/2 hour, use other 1/2 can soup.
Bake covered at 350° another 1/2 hour.
You will have a wonderful gravy.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal treats
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir constantly over heat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of peanut butter until smooth.
Add oatmeal.
Drop mixture onto wax paper with spoon.
(May add more oatmeal if needed to make easier handling.)
Cool 15 minutes.

title: caramel brownie tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place mini foil baking cups in miniature tins (36 total).
Beat butter with mixer until creamy.
On low speed, beat in sugar, eggs, melted chocolate, vanilla and salt. Gradually beat in flour.
Divide batter into baking cups, using 1 level tablespoon per cup.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until barely done.
Press one candy, bottom side up, into the center of each tart until even with top.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from tins and cool.

title: hash brown bake
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk and cream cheese.
Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth.
Combine potatoes and onions; stir into soup mixture and pour into covered baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven uncovered until cheese is melted.
Heat the fried onion rings and place on top just before serving if desired.

title: grandam verogee's springla(germany 1875)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 10 minutes in electric mixer.
Add lemon rind and baking powder.
Add enough flour so dough will roll out and press with springla (Springerle) roller or press with designs.
Cut shapes and sprinkle trays with anise seed.
Lay out cookies on tray.
Let sit overnight to dry.
Bake at 300° until lower part is bright yellow.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar. Store in tightly closed containers for up to 6 months.

title: tropical island punch
directions: Thaw concentrated limeade, pineapple and orange juices; combine in large container.
Add water and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour punch into punch bowl with block of ice.
With toothpicks, fix maraschino cherries into centers of pineapple slices.
Float pineapple, banana and lime slices on punch.

title: butter nut cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix as directed on box.
Mix flour and milk thoroughly	and
cook
to
a thick paste.
Let cool.
In large bowl beat sugar and margarine (room temperature) until fluffy. Add flour
and
milk
paste a little at a time, beating after each spoonful.
Add
pecans
and coconut.
Icing will cover 3 layers and sides.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk
in
a
medium
size
mixing bowl (reserve half of mixture for top of casserole).
Combine rice, mushrooms with liquid and half
of onion soup mix with half of soup and milk mixture.
Pour
into
a large greased casserole. Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining dry soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1
hour.
Remove
foil and bake an additional 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together the shortening and sugar and beat until creamy. Add egg and stir in mashed banana and sour milk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Pour in nuts and mix. Grease 2 loaf pans and line each with 2 thicknesses of wax paper. Pour batter into pans and bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Combine rice and soups and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Place chicken parts on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal with foil.
Bake for 2 hours in 325° oven.
Do not peek during baking.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Gradually add
milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into prepared tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove from oven and add glaze.

title: el dorado shrimp pate
directions: Add shrimp to 3 quarts rapidly boiling salted water.
Remove as soon as they turn pink and rise to the top of the water.
Do not overcook.
Peel and finely chop shrimp.
Combine shrimp, cheese, lime juice, sour cream and parsley in a blender or food processor.
Mix to a thick consistency.
Season to taste.
Spoon mixture into a mold or container.
Refrigerate for 4 hours. Remove pate from mold to serving platter.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with crackers or bread.

title: creamy caramel-pecan rolls
directions: For Topping:
In a small bowl, stir together powdered sugar and whipping cream.
Divide evenly between two (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins evenly over sugar mixture.

title: mom's "pig lickin" good cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges together with an electric mixer and pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch pieces and cook until tender; drain. Fry bacon until crisp and drain on paper towels.
Put all ingredients except bread crumbs in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Squeeze lemons.
Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale to punch bowl as needed.
Serves 150.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place meat in oil with onions and celery.
Cook slowly until light brown; drain off oil.
While meat is browning, heat rest of ingredients, stirring and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, uncovered. Baste every 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake.

title: perfection salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add sugar, salt and hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and lemon juice.
Cool. Rinse mold in cold water.
When gelatin begins to slightly thicken, add vegetables.
Pour in mold.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Unmold on lettuce or salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries and put sugar on them.
Let them set an hour or overnight.
Make pie crust.
Sprinkle flour on the bottom of pie crust.
Put in strawberries and cover with crust with slits in it.
Before putting on top crust, put some butter on top of the strawberries.
Cook until crust lightly brows at 400°.

title: apple roll dessert
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter; heat until melted.
Set aside.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk; stir until moistened. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Spread shredded apples on dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg mixture.
Roll up like a jelly roll; cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour syrup over rolls. Syrup will be absorbed in baking.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with cream.

title: frozen fruit sherbet
directions: Combine ingredients; place in freezer and stir several times over a 24 hour period.
This will keep in freezer for several weeks.
Remove from freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.
After almost set, you can put in little cups and return to freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and place in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Instead of water, mash berries.
Mix everything by hand and pour in a Bundt cake pan.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix in a sheet pan.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Crumble slightly in large punch bowl.
Pour pineapple evenly over cake. Mix pudding and pour over pineapple.
Let set for a few minutes. Spoon cherry filling evenly over pudding.
Spoon whipped topping over filling.
Chill 20 - 30 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: To mayonnaise, add sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix together.
Put flour, soda and cocoa together in the sifter.
Put in, a little bit at a time, and add milk too at sometime, until all are mixed together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and green peppers together.
Add pepperoni, mushrooms and Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Boil noodles while preparing sauce.
Drain noodles and mix all ingredients in large flat pan, like a sheet cake pan.
Heat in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Add cheese to top after heating; brown a few minutes to melt cheese.
For cheese lovers, grate extra Mozzarella and add to sauce mixture before heating.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: Place meat, onion and garlic in a 2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid or wax paper.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Stir in broth, mushrooms and chives.

title: crock-pot cheese souffle
directions: Grease crock-pot well with margarine.
Layer bread cubes and shredded cheeses in crock-pot.
Mix together eggs, evaporated milk, milk and salt.
Pour over bread and cheese in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low heat setting for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve hot.

title: tomato egg flower soup
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water to cover for 30 minutes; drain and reserve 1 cup liquid.
Cut off and discard stems and dice caps. Set aside.
In a 3 quart pot, bring broth, wine, reserved mushroom soaking liquid and mushrooms to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add tomato and cook for 1 minute.
Add cornstarch solution and cook, stirring, until soup boils and thickens slightly.
Remove from heat and slowly drizzle in egg, stirring constantly.
Season with sesame oil, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Tip:
To peel tomato, blanch in boiling water for 30 seconds, then rinse in cold water before stripping off skin.
Cut tomato in half crosswise. Gently squeeze each half to remove seeds before dicing.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pan roasted chicken and vegetables
directions: *For reduced fat, use nonstick pan.
Remove chicken skin and reduce oil to 2 tablespoons.

title: gulliver's corn
directions: Combine first six ingredients in pot and bring to a boil. Simmer for 5 minutes. Melt butter and add flour. Add to corn. Mix well and serve. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix together, then add the Eagle Brand milk.
Press in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Makes 1 batch.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 4 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In large ovenproof pot, mix onion soup with enough water to fill bottom of pot.
Add chicken parts.
Bake at 350° until chicken is about done.
Remove from oven.
Add soups, water and rice.
Mix together well.
Return to oven and bake until rice is done.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In a large skillet cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Stir in beans, soup, 1/4 cup water, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a covered pan cook potatoes in boiling salted water just until tender; drain.
Mash while hot; stir in egg.
Add enough milk to make potatoes fluffy, yet stiff enough to hold their shape.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drop potatoes in mounds atop meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Boil whole
squash
in
salted water just until tender. Cool; split
lengthwise
and
scoop out pulp.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and squash pulp. Stuff shells with
this
mixture;
top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts in salted water, about 30 minutes. Remove skin and bones, cut into small pieces, set aside and save broth.
Saute onion and green peppers in butter.
Add pimento, mushroom soup, 1/2 can chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Keep on warm or low heat.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until tender, drain.
Add chicken pieces, spaghetti, drained, and sharp cheddar cheese to mixture in skillet.
Stir mixture on low heat until cheese melts; pour in 13 x 9 inch casserole dish.
Top with medium cheddar cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar in bowl of food processor, fitted with steel blade. Process until blended.
Add pepperoni and sun-dried tomatoes.
Pulse until well mixed.
Form into a ball and roll in ground pecans.

title: spareribs "aloha"
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients and let stand to blend flavor.
Pour over ribs.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, basting frequently to glaze ribs.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Cook beef or chicken in an iron skillet until browned.
Add seasoning, beans and tomato sauce.
Cook until hot.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Spoon corn bread batter over cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until corn bread is done.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Clean and batter chicken breasts with flour, salt and pepper. Butter a casserole; place chicken in it and bake for 30 minutes. Then pour Pet milk mixed with cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over and bake until cheese melts.

title: quick zucchini bread
directions: Drain zucchini well
and
combine with sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in	a
large
bowl.
Sift
flour,
soda,
salt and cinnamon together.	Add
to
zucchini
mixture and blend well. Stir in nuts,
rind
and raisins.
Divide batter into two well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 70 minutes	or
until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in
pans
10	minutes.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly on wire racks.

title: corn chowder
directions: Slice potatoes thin and boil until tender in small amount of water.
Brown onion in butter.
Add milk, onion and corn to the potatoes.
Do not drain potatoes.
Makes enough for 3 to 6 people.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar in a small glass bowl; set aside (do not use plastic!).
Mix 1 cup sugar, margarine, salt and boiling water together until margarine melts. Add the cold water and beaten eggs to the sugar-water mixture. When cool, add yeast mixture.
Adding about 1 1/2 cups at a time, sift about 8 cups of flour into yeast mixture.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
Oil dough and let rise double.
Punch down; let rise a second time.
Punch down and roll out onto floured board.

title: sugar-free cherry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and over medium heat, stir until mixture is hot and mixed.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cover with pie crust (cut into strips or whole vented).
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°; reduce to 350° and bake 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake dessert
directions: Sprinkle crumbs on bottom of rectangular cake pan.
Chill until very cold.
Mix jello, sugar, boiling water and lemon juice. Chill until partially thick.
Add evaporated milk; beat until thick.
Add to thickened jello mixture; spread over chilled crumbs and sprinkle lightly with crumbs.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Brown beef, seasoned as you like.
Combine soups, milk, enchilada sauce and 1/2 the cheese over medium heat until cheese melts.
In a casserole pan layer corn chips on the bottom of pan. Combine soup mixture and beef, then pour over chips.
Top with the rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for at least 25 minutes.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine sugar, mint leaves and boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add raspberries and lemonade; stir until thawed. Strain; pour into punch bowl.
Add water.
Chill thoroughly. Float scoops of sherbet when ready to serve.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown meat until redness is gone.
Drain excess grease.
Cook peppers and onions until they are still crisp.
Add tomato sauce, kidney beans, garlic salt and chili powder.
Simmer 45 minutes at medium temperature.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in salt, shortening and 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour (first with spoon, then by hand) to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)
Punch down dough; round up and let rise until almost double, about 45 minutes. Punch down; cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Roll dough into rectangle, 15 x 10 inches.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side.
Pinch edge firmly to seal. Roll gently back and forth to taper ends.
Place loaf on lightly greased cookie sheet.
If desired, make 1/4-inch slashes across loaf at 2-inch intervals.
Brush with cold water.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Brush with cold water.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat egg white and 2 tablespoons cold water slightly; brush over loaf.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool on wire rack.

title: baked spinach
directions: Boil spinach, sage and thyme in a little water, about 5 minutes. Put in colander and drain. Make a paste with flour and a little milk. Add eggs and beat. Put in milk and spinach. Put into greased baking pan using bacon grease. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. When firm, stir a little and cook 10 more minutes. Place bacon strips on top and brown.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Pour a little oil in frying pan.
Cook vegetables until almost done.
Add chicken.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch and a little water.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice.
(Beef cubes or turkey cutlets can also be used.)

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool; punch holes in cake. Pour pineapple and juice on top of cake.
Mix milk, cream cheese and pudding.
Spread over pineapple.
Top with whipped topping.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel rind from melon.
Cut off green outer rind and any pink flesh.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cover with water and add alum. Stir and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices and bring to a boil.
Add the rind and bring to a boil again.
Place in jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine milk and eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and corn.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
Can be microwaved.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine cake mix, flour, eggs, oil, molasses and ginger in large bowl (mixture will be soft).
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pecan spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices together into a large mixing bowl.
Place butter in a large mixing bowl and cream until soft.
Gradually beat in the sugar and eggs.
Stir in pecans.
Add the flour mixture alternately with molasses and milk, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Add
boiled
chicken
to
cornbread and equal amount of loaf bread
(week-old
bread
is better to use).
Let it set a few hours after crumbling to dry out.
Cook chopped onions and celery in skillet until tender, but do not cook too long.
Add boiling broth
to
bread crumbs;
stir to
make
smooth.
Add beaten eggs, onion and celery, then more broth until it's real soupy
and thin. Add pepper and sage to taste
and
salt,
if needed.
Place in flat pan or casserole dish.
Bake
at
350° until brown.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Marinate mushrooms in Italian dressing; drain. Combine crabmeat, 1/2 cup of bread crumbs, eggs, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice. Fill mushrooms. Top with remaining bread crumbs; bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Yields 20 appetizers or 4 main course servings.

title: cinnamon rolls or dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve 2 teaspoons sugar in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add dry yeast.
Let set until bubbles form.
Beat this with remaining water, sugar, 2 1/2 cups flour and milk with a wire whip beater. Let set until light and bubbly.
Add shortening and eggs; beat again.
Mix salt with 3 cups flour; add, using a slotted spoon. Let dough rest 10 minutes.
Knead dough, using a small amount of flour, if needed.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Shape into cinnamon rolls or dinner rolls.

title: m.k.c.'s creamed mushroom chicken breasts
directions: Cut large chicken breast in half; roll in flour and stir-fry in shortening (1/2 cup).
Cook until golden brown, then put in casserole dish.
In stir-fry drippings, combine next 9 ingredients.
Pour over all chicken breasts; cover with foil. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, then sprinkle for topping 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over all; cover.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°; let set 15 minutes and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine ingredients except bacon and olives.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour.
Never fails.
Delicious!

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Break the broccoli and cauliflower into flowerettes.
Combine the raw vegetables; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: delicious raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Combine the oats, flour, orange peel, cinnamon and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the raisins (dough will be stiff).
Drop by level tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: fettucini alfredo di parma(serves 4 as side dish)
directions: Put cream in saute pan over low heat.
Gently and slowly stir in Parmesan cheese (a little at a time) until cheese sauce appears. Add 1/3 cup wine and the Prosciutto, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked capellini, black pepper and parsley.
Stir and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve.
Sprinkle Romano cheese on top.
Delicious.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper on steak. Pound steak and brown on both sides in oil. Add other ingredients. Cook in Miro-Matic pot for 30 minutes or until steak is tender. Serves 2.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg and oil.
Mix flour and sugar with liquid ingredients.
At this point, refrigerate or use some of mixture.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. When baking, use buttered muffin tins.
Fill tins 3/4 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen muffins.

title: wild strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar, mixing thoroughly; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix pectin with water in large saucepan, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Quickly add fruit, continuing to stir and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour jam into sterilized glass or plastic containers with tight fitting lids. Cover immediately.
Let container stand at room temperature for 24 hours then place jam in freezer.

title: honeydew's favorite roast
directions: Coat roast with seasoning.
For best results, use a meat thermometer.
Put roast in pan.
Pour water around it.
Cover pan. In the oven, bake at 325° until temperature reads 170° (well done), 35 minutes per pound.
I use a slow cooker.
Place roast in it in the morning, turn it to between low and medium.
Let it cook until supper time.
This is really good and saves time.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix on medium speed the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add water and vanilla.
Add grated pears, then dry ingredients.
Add nuts last. Grease and flour 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be frozen!

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Beat eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into baking dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 250° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sausage spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground round and drain off fat.
Add sausage and drain off fat.
Saute seasoning.
Add meat and the remaining ingredients to the crock-pot and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix cooked spinach, stuffing mix, onion, eggs, butter, cheese, garlic salt, parsley seasoning, thyme and pepper in bowl.
Chill until firm.
Shape into balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 50.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; stir until smooth.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add beets to hot sauce and let stand for 30 minutes before serving.
Add butter.

title: fluffy white icing(try this with black walnut cake)
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick, stirring constantly. Cool.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Add pineapple
juice
and boiling water to Jell-O.
Mix milk with
pudding
and	whip
until
thick.
Add Cool Whip to pudding after thick.
Mix Jell-O and pudding mixtures together and beat slowly; add pineapple.
Chill 1 hour.
Place oranges on top.

title: microwave custard pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Microwave on 5 level for 20 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese no bake cake
directions: Top with crushed pineapple.
Add sugar to cornstarch; cook until thick.
Spread over top.
Cool well.
Cut in squares.
Keeps well.

title: chocolate cloud cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Stir together and let cool a little.
Fold into thawed whipped topping.
Shape a spoonful around each almond and roll in coconut or very fine crumbs.
Place clouds on waxed paper and refrigerate, covered, until firm.
Delicious!

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and vanilla and stir until well blended.
Stir in margarine, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Cover with foil after 40 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: special strawberry trifle
directions: Cut angel food cakes in cubes (about 8 cups). Set aside. Arrange enough strawberry slices, cut side down, to line the lower edge of a 14 cup trifle bowl. Place strawberry slices against the inside edge of trifle bowl for an attractive appearance. Arrange half of cake cubes in bowl. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons schnapps. Combine remaining strawberry slices and 2 tablespoons schnapps; let stand 30 minutes. Drain strawberries, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid. Top cake with half of strawberries. Spoon 2 cups chilled custard over strawberries. Top with remaining cake cubes; sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons schnapps. Spoon remaining strawberries over cake cubes. Combine preserves and reserved strawberry liquid, stirring well; spread over layer of strawberries. Spoon remaining custard over preserves. Beat whipping cream until foamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form. Add 2 teaspoons schnapps, and beat well; spread sweetened whipping cream over trifle. Garnish with strawberries and toasted almonds. Serve immediately. Yield 14 servings.

title: green rice
directions: Mix together well in pan.
Bake in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine; add flour, milk, sugar and cinnamon (mixture will be thick).
Pour into baking dish and add peaches.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Add in cocktail peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Ready to eat when cooled.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: Note:
You will need 10 wooden skewers.

title: larry's baked ham
directions: Mix prepared mustard and 1/4 cup brown sugar; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over and in sliced ham.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pour mustard and brown sugar mixture over ham and bake 15 minutes more.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Blend in sugar and shortening.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll dough and cut into crescent shape with cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven for 15 minutes.
(Do not brown.) When cool, dip in powdered sugar.

title: nell's canned apple pie filling
directions: Blend together all but apples.
Cook until thick.
Peel and dice apples ahead.
Pack diced apples in jars.
Add hot thickener to jars.
Process 20 minutes for quarts and 15 minutes for pints in standard old type blue canner.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together.
(Use all the juice in both pineapple and blueberries).
Let jell.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in fruit, raisins, noodles and butter.

title: teddy snack mix
directions: Place cookies, popcorn and pretzels in large baking pan.
Stir together melted butter and cinnamon.
Pour butter cinnamon mixture over cookie mixture; toss evenly.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool completely.
Add raisins and M&M's.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 7 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese.
Gradually add Bisquick, working in with hands.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix last four ingredients with jello mixture.
Pour in mold or fruit bowl.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: grandma's grape-nuts bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Let stand while mixing next 4.
Then mix all together and let stand 20 minutes before putting into oven.
Use long thin bread pan or 2 small thin pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and pumpkin.
Mix thoroughly and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jumbo stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Brown ground sirloin (you may add onion, garlic and oregano to taste).
Drain off grease and let cool.
Beat eggs and stir in the cheeses and the ground meat.
Pour a small amount of spaghetti sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Stuff shells with ground beef mixture and place in dish.
Top shells with remaining spaghetti sauce.
Top with additional Parmesan if desired.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbling.
Freezes well.

title: almond cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, then add the oil.
Next, add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Last, mix in the almond filling.
Bake in ungreased angel food pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: meaty porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, 1/2 c. water, onion, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Heat oil in skillet, brown meat balls on all sides.
Stir together tomato sauce, celery salt, worchestershire sauce and 1 c. water.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 45 mins.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and pudding in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture then stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
For chocolate-chocolate chip cookies, substitute chocolate pudding instead of vanilla.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix together.
Beat 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 thin layers.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: easy cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add flour (a small amount at a time). Add vanilla and lemon flavor. Place tablespoonfuls full of dough on ungreased cookie sheet and press with a glass dipped in ice water. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese together, then add Bisquick (mixes up better this way).
Form small balls; bake on ungreased sheet for 15 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 90.

title: bread pudding for dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease inside of baking dish with butter or margarine.
(The more the better!!!)
Cube slices of bread and put in dish.

title: huff-puffer supper
directions: Cook burger, green pepper and onion in small amount of oil until transparent.
Stir in salt, zucchini, mushrooms, oregano, garlic and chili powder.
Cover and let cook until zucchini is tender, about 7 minutes, then add corn, beans, olives and tomato. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in the cheeses.
Fill pocket bread that has been cut in halves and serve.

title: coconut bars
directions: Cream together butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar in mixing bowl until light
and
fluffy.
Sift
together
3/4 cup flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture along with oats. Press into bottom
of greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Beat eggs in another bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread over crust. Bake
in
oven
for
25 to 30 minutes until brown on top. Cool
in
pan.
Cut
into
1 1/2 x 1-inch bars. Makes 20 bars.

title: exotic luncheon salad
directions: Mix water chestnuts with chicken; add grapes, celery and almonds, reserving a few for garnish.
Mix mayonnaise with curry and soy sauce.
Combine with chicken mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Place on lettuce.
Garnish with reserved almonds and pineapple chunks.
Serves 12.

title: homemade pierogis
directions: Mix dough ingredients in bowl.
Cover and let set for an hour. Roll dough and cut in circles or squares.
Put filling in and fold over sealing edges tight.
Drop in boiling water, cook until they come to the top.
Cook a few at a time.
Drain.
May be frozen before cooking.
When done, serve with melted butter or saute onions in butter and pour over.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Add shortening, egg and 1/2 cup water.
Blend with mixer just until blended.
Add apples; stir in by hand.
Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of each muffin. Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: country chicken
directions: Use a large skillet with a cover.
Heat 2 to 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Coat chicken on both sides with Italian-style bread crumbs and brown in hot oil.
Mix and pour the next 3 ingredients over browned chicken.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: summer squash patties
directions: Combine first six ingredients, beating until smooth.
Stir in squash.
Add onion and pepper.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken; place on platter.
In plastic bag, mix instant potatoes, thyme and garlic salt; shake well.
Prepare cookie sheets, lined with aluminum foil.
Set oven to 450°.
Put chicken in plastic bag, shake, take out and place on cookie sheet (not touching).
When golden, with turkey baster, put drops of water (keeps moist) on each piece.
Takes 1 hour to 1 1/2 hour.

title: johnnie's batter for rellenos
directions: Beat egg yolks separately from whites.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add enough flour to egg yolks to make a paste.
Add egg whites; mix well.
Dip stuffed green chilies in batter; fasten with a toothpick.
Dip in flour and deep fry.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Place marshmallows on bottom of 9 x 13 greased pan. Combine strawberries and jello. Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Mix chopped vegetables, onions, green pepper and shredded cheese and put in 10-inch pie plate, greased.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick and salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dressing anytime
directions: In a sauce pot mix the two cans of cream of chicken soup, 2 sticks margarine, onion diced, boiled eggs, season packet from Stove Top stuffing, and 2 C water. Bring to a slow boil.

title: chocolate cherry drops
directions: Melt baking chocolate over hot water.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg; blend well.
Stir in vanilla and baking chocolate; beat until combined.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into chocolate mixture.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: tamale lentil soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine uncooked lentils and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to boiling; reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, then drain.
Stir in remaining water, corn, beans, zucchini, celery, carrot, tomatoes, tomato soup, onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, cumin and pepper.
Return to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Serve with Fritos.

title: no bake cherry cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften, add sugar and vanilla, beat until soft and smooth.
Beat heavy cream until stiff, fold into cream cheese mixture.
Take 1 package ladyfingers and line spring-form pan.
Take 1/2 of the other package, break in half and line bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over broken pieces, take the other 1/2 of ladyfinger package and break into pieces.
Put on rest of creamy mixture.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours, covering with Saran Wrap.
Pour cherry filling on top before serving.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place hot tamales in bottom of a medium baking dish.
Add corn and spread over the tamales.
Layer it with your favorite cheese.
Cover and bake until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and mix to blend. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture, alternately with sour cream to which vanilla has been added.
Mix just to blend walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn 1/2 dough into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 crunch mixture over this.
Pour rest of batter; top with remaining crunch.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: *Can just use 2 cans chicken soup.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Cut cake in the middle with thread.
Spread a layer of cherry pie filling and Cool Whip in the middle and put top back on. Spread with Cool Whip and drizzle with cherry pie filling.

title: crepes
directions: Combine flour, milk, salt, eggs and melted butter in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Pour scant 1/4 cup batter into hot, lightly greased crepe pan.
Tilt pan to spread batter evenly. Bake until light brown on both sides; stack between waxed paper. May sprinkle with sugar or confectioners sugar or fill with jam, fresh fruit or preserves.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: creamed squash and onion soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine the onion, squash, butter, and water. Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender but not mushy. Combine flour with 1/2 cup milk. Mix well and then add to squash mixture, stirring well.
Add remaining milk, cheese, salt and black pepper.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: fluffy apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple, Jell-O and sugar.
Heat until dissolved.
Add baby food, cream cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: texas candy
directions: Mix and stir on low for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, pecans, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: diabetic cake(no sugar)
directions: Cook the raisins until dry.
Drain well.
Drain fruit cocktail, then add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Add to rest of ingredients.	Bake in round angle cake pan for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise (like a large sandwich).
Mix other ingredients and spread over rolls.
Replace top and wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, zucchini and vanilla together.
Mix dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture.
Then mix nuts and raisins. Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Chop onion, pepper, celery and garlic fine and saute in oil until soft.
Add the chopped raw shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cook until shrimp is done, 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove bread from water and squeeze out water; add to mixture a little a time, mixing well. Add parsley.
Let cook 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool, then add eggs and mix well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin until barely done.
Peel and grate coarsely.
In medium saucepan, heat butter and cheese until almost melted.
Remove and blend in onion, sour cream, salt and pepper. Stir lightly into potatoes.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can be made day ahead.
Also good reheated.

title: sweet potato tipsy
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, peel, mash	and whip, adding cream,
butter and brown sugar, plus wine.	Turn
into
greased casserole.	Bake at 350° until heated through,
about
25 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well. Fold in blueberries with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with topping.

title: potatoes
directions: You cook them.
You stir them and put butter on them.
You eat them.

title: junior's famous cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cream the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add the combined sugar and cornstarch.
Beat in egg, then vanilla and heavy cream.
Pour into a well-greased 7-inch pan with graham cracker or zwieback crust on bottom of pan. Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until the top is golden brown.
Cool for about 3 hours, then refrigerate until 15 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!!

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Add ingredients as given and do not mix until all is in bowl. Mix until smooth and put into a Bundt or 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for approximately 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: ground meat stew
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in bottom of baking dish.
Layer ground meat.
Layer sliced onions.
Layer mixed vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion soup mix.
Pour tomato sauce and water over meat and vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherries with 1/2 cup plain flour.
Add dates and rest of ingredients.
Pack in loaf pan and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, and milk for sauce. Put chicken into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with stuffing.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pie dough fried fruit tarts
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar, then add eggs, Crisco and milk.
Let dough set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Roll as thin as possible (it won't tear up).
Cut around a saucer.
Put fruit on dough, take fingers and wet edge of dough with water.
Mash together with a fork.
Fry in hot Crisco (they brown fast).

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into fairly large balls. Then roll in corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Better if made a day ahead and reheated.
Serves 4.

title: blue cheese spread with walnuts
directions: Grate walnuts using food processor with shredding disk or rotary grater and set aside. Combine the white and Blue cheese in a dish and mash together with a fork, incorporating the cognac and a little salt and pepper. When the mixture is smooth, add the walnuts and chives. Mix again until well blended. Spoon into a serving bowl. Serve with breadsticks, fresh veggies or toast points. Serves 8.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Reserve 3 cups of the flour.
In a large container, combine all the fruit.
Sprinkle the remaining 2 cups flour over the fruit and toss to coat each piece.
Mix in the pecans and set aside. Cream butter until smooth and creamy.
Add brown sugar gradually and continue beating until sugar granules disappear.
Beat in the egg yolks.
Add evaporated milk and lemon juice.
Combine reserved 3 cups flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Sift together, then stir into butter mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into butter-flour mixture until well blended.
Add fruit mixture and blend thoroughly.

title: pizza dipping sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a small saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes.

title: flaming dessert
directions: In crystal dish, put cake in the middle of the dish. Pour cherry pie filling around cake. Put vanilla ice cream in the middle of the cake. Put sugar cubes in a tablespoon and pour lemon extract over them. Place the sugar cubes in the center of the ice cream. Light with a match. When flames burn down, remove sugar cubes and serve. Very good.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or chips. Store in tightly covered container in the refrigerator.

title: the best tex-mex dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill for several hours or make day before. Serve with Frito dippers.

title: cooked dressing for potato salad
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vinegar very slowly.
Stir and cook until mixture begins to thicken.

title: garden salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cut up vegetables.
Mix well.
Allow to cool.
Place in a gallon jar. Refrigerate.
Serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Combine and mix well.
Chill.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Dip cookie ball in mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet. Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish put uncooked rice, corn (salt and peppered), tomato sauce mixed with 1/2 cup water, chopped onion and pepper and ground beef (uncooked) spread over the top; salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Cover meat with bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or longer, until bacon is crisp.

title: pasta with shrimp, tomato and arugula(double for 2)
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat the oil over moderately high heat until it is hot, but not smoking.
In it, saute the shrimp, the garlic and the pepper flakes, stirring for 1 to 2 minutes or until the shrimp are pink and almost cooked through and transfer the shrimp with a slotted spoon to a bowl.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add oil and mix with a fork.
Stir in raisins and seed.
Mix buttermilk and egg together; add to flour mixture.
Turn onto floured board and knead 10 times.
Form a ball and then flatten lightly.
Put into an 8-inch round pan. Cut a cross on top.
Brush with oil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Mix dry ingredients (first 4).
Coat each rolled piece of chicken breast with dry mixture.
Dip in beaten egg/milk mixture, then roll in crumbs.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Place broccoli in buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to directions on the box.
Drain and cut up.
Combine all other ingredients.
Toss the dressing over the pasta.
Chill.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg whites and cold water until frothy. Toss nutmeats in mixture until well coated. Mix remaining ingredients together. Cover nutmeats with dry mixture. Spread into buttered pan. Toast in 350° oven for 1/2 hour, turning 3 or 4 times.

title: meat cup with creamed potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Line ungreased muffin tin with mixture to about 1/4-inch thickness.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Pack quart jars as tight as possible.
Add salt, spices and garlic.
Top with dill and fill jar with cold water.
Seal.

title: angel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Beat in salt and cream of tartar.
Add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into lightly buttered 8-inch pie pan to form a nest-like shell.
Build up sides at least 1/2-inch above edge of pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate-pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix together flour and baking soda.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter, and water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; immediately remove from heat.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in the 1 cup chocolate morsels and the vanilla until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar well; toss with vegetables. Refrigerate overnight or longer.

title: apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients and turn into a well-greased casserole.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes.
Serve warm. Serves 4.

title: baked tamales
directions: Boil 2 cups water and salt.
Stir in corn meal until mixture resembles mush.
Season meat with chili powder.
Put layer of corn meal in baking dish.
Add meat.
Cover with balance of corn meal. Pour in beef stock.
Bake in 350° oven until nicely browned.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat liquid ingredients together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and bran.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute shrimp in butter for 3 to 5 minutes over low heat, stirring frequently.
Add soups and stir until well blended.
Stir in sour cream, curry powder and parsley.
Continue stirring until mixture is piping hot, then serve immediately over hot cooked rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and eggs, then blend in next 6 ingredients. Add raisins, dates and chopped nuts last. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven 12 minutes or until done.

title: herb vinegar
directions: Combine in a jar with a lid.
Let stand 24 hours; remove garlic.

title: date coconut delight cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed, while still warm punch holes in top of cake with wooden handle.
Pour over warm cake the milk and cream of coconut.
Refrigerate over night;
before serving spread with cool whip and sprinkle with angel coconut and chopped pecans.

title: sauerkraut ham balls
directions: In large bowl, combine ham, sauerkraut, onion and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic powder and pepper.
Stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill at least one hour.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Coat with flour.
Beat eggs and milk.
Dip balls into egg mixture and roll in remaining crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.
