title: beans and wiener biscuit casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sliced wieners, pork and beans, ketchup, onion and brown sugar.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon hot bean mixture into an ungreased 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Separate canned biscuits and arrange over bean mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and no longer doughy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; shape into loaf and place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf
pan.	Bake
at
350°	for
45 to 50 minutes.	Let stand 10 to 15 minutes, then slice.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Add Coke last.
Fold in gently. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Ice with chocolate frosting. You may make layers or sheet cake.

title: rum pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, syrup, butter and soda in heavy buttered 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook, without stirring, to 236°, or until soft ball is formed when small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add rum or rum extract and salt.
Beat vigorously until candy thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Place waxed paper on newspaper and pralines will come up easily.

title: lime yogurt pie
directions: Combine gelatin and yogurt.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread into crust.
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Bake in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased) for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with utility fork.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: boursin cheese spread
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add garlic. Process until finely chopped, stopping once to scrape down sides. Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients; process until smooth, stopping twice to scrape down sides.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In top of double boiler, melt butter and flour.
Blend well. Add milk slowly stirring constantly until thick.
Add soup, pimentos, mushrooms, salt, pepper and chicken cut in large pieces. Mix well.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or toast tips.
Freezes well.
Thaw and heat.
Serve with peas and cranberry sauce.
Serves 4.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Make this up the night before and serve the next evening.

title: mezes
directions: Bake Kefalotiri in olive oil at 300° in the oven until the cheese is stringy like Mozzarella on a pizza.
Take out of oven; add garlic bits and fresh ground pepper.
Use French bread to dip in the melted cheese as if you were eating a fondue.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, butter and 2 eggs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine
raisins
and
water.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Stir in salad oil or margarine.
Cool to lukewarm. Stir in sugar
and	egg.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients. Beat into raisin
mixture.
Stir
in nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan, 10
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or	until
nicely
browned.
Cool and cut into bars and dust with powdered sugar or frost.

title: swiss steak in sour cream
directions: Dredge steak with flour and season with salt and pepper. Brown on both sides in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover pan and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Place egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and cold water in double boiler.
Cook over medium heat.
Beat with electric mixer until stiff, approximately 7 minutes.
Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla after removing from heat.

title: doral's chicken, crab and swiss delight
directions: Marinate the skinned chicken breasts for 30 minutes in the prepared Good Seasons Italian salad dressing.
Cook rice and keep warm.
Drench breasts in beaten eggs.
Mix bread crumbs, salt and pepper together and dredge the chicken in the crumb mixture.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and scald in water with some vinegar in it.
Drain again.
Then put in the remaining ingredients and cook until tender and can.

title: baked macaroni and cheese squares
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. To hot macaroni, add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese. Mix well. Cook and stir over medium heat 5 minutes, until bouillon cube dissolves and cheese melts. Turn into a greased 8 x 8 pan. Top with rest of cheese and bake 20 minutes or until bubbly at 300°. Let stand 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: butter fingers
directions: Mix ingredients for crust well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: feather spice cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff and glossy.
In another bowl stir shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch layer pans or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until done.

title: brenda's pumpkin cake roll
directions: Place eggs in bowl.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed. Gradually sprinkle in sugar and beat for 4 minutes.
Reduce to stirring and add pumpkin.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Stir together with mixer, and gradually add flour mixture to egg mixture for about 1 minute.
Line a 9 x 13- x 3/4-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper and grease.
Pour the mixture into the pan and bake at 375° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove from the oven and immediately turn onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove the waxed paper and roll the cake and towel together; cool completely.

title: holiday cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually stir in pineapple and 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into ball and roll in 1 cup pecans.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with twists of pineapple slices, cherries and parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: *I use equal amounts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 425°.
Put cheese in middle.

title: fried zucchini sticks
directions: Cut zucchini into French fry-style pieces.
Use 4 bowls.
Use one bowl for milk, one for breadcrumbs, one for egg and one for flour.
Dip zucchini in milk, then flour, then beaten egg and then in breadcrumbs.

title: shortbread dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 325°; cool.
Mix together vanilla pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour over cooled crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Layer Cool Whip over ice cream.
Sprinkle crushed candy over Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise together. Put in a casserole dish.

title: jam-cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 3 layers (round pans) at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil hard for 4 minutes if using whole milk, 6 minutes if using skim milk.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until it begins to thicken.
Pour into 11 x 14-inch buttered container. Serves 36.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together just before adding dressing.

title: strawberry angel food torte
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, sugar and salt.
Fold in whipping cream.
Put a layer of angel food pieces on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over half the strawberry mixture.
Add remaining layer of angel food pieces and top with remaining strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Top with Cool Whip or whipping cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Cut chilies into thin strips; remove seeds.
In a lightly greased 9-inch square pan, alternately layer chilies with cheese, starting and ending with cheese. Beat eggs, milk and flour together.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until firm.
Cut into small squares and serve warm.

title: non-alcohol "champagne"
directions: Mix equal parts white grape juice and ginger ale in punch bowl over ice.

title: cashew chicken balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl.
Use a teaspoon to scoop out amount to form balls.
Roll in cashews. Chill.
Yields 20 appetizers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes with 1 stick margarine.
Add salt, pepper, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cornflakes mixed with 1/2 stick melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers well; drain whole cucumbers.
Place in a large plastic container (like kitchen trash can).
Pour apple cider vinegar over cucumbers to cover.
Place in out of the way place and cover with cloth.
Let set 6 weeks.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix together in large Tupperware mixing bowl.
Then add store bought 5-inch angel food cake.
Push cake down into mixture in bowl (gently).
Seal and burp bowl; let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a large pot, fry diced bacon until brown and crispy.
Drain off almost all grease. Add celery, carrots and onion.
Saute a few minutes.
Slowly add 1 cup water to avoid splattering. Add bouillon cube, salt and pepper. Cover and cook over medium heat while peeling the potatoes.

Add potatoes and a little more water, if needed. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove from heat and mash well. Return to heat and add 1 cup milk, stirring well with a wooden spoon. Add cornstarch to remaining cup of milk.
Mix well. Add to soup. Add cubed cheese. Cook on low heat until cheese melts and soup thickens. Stir all the time. Recipe can be doubled.

title: singapore slings
directions: Dilute to taste with soda water.
Old family recipe.

title: beef barbecue for canning
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add other ingredients and 4 cups beef broth or water (or more, if necessary).
Steam 10 minutes and pack in jars.
Seal.
Makes about 9 quarts.
Boil about 2 hours in hot water bath.

title: cream filling (for cream puffs)
directions: Fold powdered sugar into whipped cream.
May also use 1 package Dream Whip.

title: barbecue salami
directions: Bake salami in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Baste every 20 minutes or so.
Serve it sliced, with crackers or cocktail bread. Everyone will love it.

title: original toll house chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: In a large pan, combine sugar, milk and butter over medium heat.
Stir until boiling.
Boil hard for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add shaved chocolate and chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Add marshmallow, nuts and vanilla. Blend; do not beat.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.
Very easy and very good!

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite-size pieces.
Put 1/2 in the bottom of a large baking pan.
Crumble the chopped meat over the cabbage. Add onion, rice and tomatoes.
Cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour soups and water over the top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dressing for lettuce
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients and add egg.
Toss on fresh garden lettuce.

title: my favorite salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, cottage cheese and jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Garnish with mandarin oranges, mint leaves, etc. Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in nuts and form ball.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Refrigerate until set up, 1 or 2 hours.
Roll up into a ball.
Roll in the walnuts.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: shrimp and vegetable scampi
directions: Pat shrimp dry and set aside.
Place bell pepper in center of a 12-inch microwaveable plate.
Arrange zucchini in an even layer around pepper.
Sprinkle pepper with water and cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on high 5 to 6 minutes or until slightly softened.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add 1/3 cup evaporated milk and oleo.
Put half mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk.
Spread on hot cake.
Spread nuts and chocolate chips on top of this.
Pour rest of batter on top of this.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Needs no icing.

title: golden parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease baking pan.
Mix cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter/margarine.
Then coat with cheese mixture and place in pan.
Pour any remaining margarine over coated chicken.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn. Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned cookies with fruit
directions: Mix first three items; pour on margarine in pan.
Pour large can of fruit.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: papa's bag
directions: Oil inside of cooking bag.
Place fish filets flat inside bag; add salt, pepper, hot sauce and garlic.
Layer tomatoes, onions and peppers over filets.
Seal bag and place on baking sheet; cut slits in bag.
Place in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.
Bag should swell and balloon when done.
Remove fish and veggies with slotted spoon and serve over rice.

title: bourbon bread pudding with butterscotch sauce
directions: Trim crust from bread using a serrated knife and discard crust.
Cut bread in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until toasted.
Combine skim milk, brown sugar, bourbon, vanilla extract and eggs in a large bowl; stir well.
Add bread cubes and raisins; toss gently.
Cover and chill 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 450° and grease muffin pans or 8 custard cups. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer, combine butter and sugar until very well blended.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and milk, beating until well blended.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups or 8 custard cups.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 5 minutes and then reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until muffins spring back when lightly touched.
Makes 12 medium or 8 jumbo muffins.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Mix together with remaining ingredients. Put in casserole dish and cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Mix milk and Jell-O. Add nuts and coconut.
Chill 2 hours. Shape into balls.
Roll in red sugar and dip stem in green sugar.

title: macaroni-cheese-ham salad
directions: In bowl, combine macaroni, ham, cheese, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento and pickle relish.
Blend together mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Add to macaroni mixture, toss and chill.

title: chocolate icebox pie - lyle's restaurant
directions: Beat one egg with sugar and margarine at high speed for 5 minutes.
(Be sure of timing.)
Add other egg, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Beat again at high speed for another 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Mix whipping cream with vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar and beat at high speed until soft peaks form.
Spread whipped cream mixture on pie.

title: rhubarb-custard pie(makes 9-inch pie)
directions: Roll out bottom crust and line pie pan.
Roll out top crust and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat with egg.
Add oatmeal, milk, dry onion soup and salt. Mix well.
Make into loaf.
Put into baking pan.
Pour catsup over meat.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples; put into pie plate.
Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, and put on top of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into a large mixing bowl; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy on low speed of electric mixer.
Sift flour and measure; sift again with salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour mixture at a time to the creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
When all flour has been added, remove electric mixer and fold in chopped pecans and raw chopped apples.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan lined on the bottom with waxed paper. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn slightly cooled cake out on a cake rack; remove the waxed paper and thoroughly cool, then frost.

title: meatball yummies
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and barbecue sauce. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Combine 1/3 cup barbecue sauce, light brown sugar and butter or margarine with meatballs in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until meatballs are done.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas in graham cracker shell evenly in crust.
Whip cream with sugar and vanilla.
Whip until cream is thick enough to cut with a knife. Put over bananas evenly.
You can garnish with a little brown coconut. Brown the coconut in oven first.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool slightly in pans. Wrap in aluminum foil and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Cook over low heat until thick.
Use a heavy pan and stir constantly. Fill a baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake at 400° until the meringue is lightly browned for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grilled mushrooms
directions: Take a whole clean mushroom and wrap with foil and place on grill for 15 minutes. Open and drain liquid. Season with garlic salt, season salt and cayenne pepper. Place pats of butter and Velveeta on each. Rewrap and place back on grill.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk, beating well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and spices; add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cake in pan; sprinkle over the top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cake will be quite moist.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put warm water, shortening, yeast and salt.
Let stand until shortening melts and yeast softens.
Give it an occasional stir.
Work in flour gradually.
Knead dough on floured board until smooth.
Place dough in an oiled bowl.
Brush top with oil, cover and let rise in a warm place away from drafts, until double in size.
Takes about 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch dough down, divide it according to the type of pan used.
Oil pans.
Roll out each portion of dough on a lightly floured board just the size of the pan and put in pan.
If dough springs back once it is in the pan, work it into shape with your hand until it fits.
Give the dough a light sprinkling of oil and spread with Basic Sauce.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 450° oven.
Makes two standard size pizzas.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Triscuits, together.
Spread mixture on Triscuits.
Place under broiler until bubbling. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Melt oleo. Mix in sugar and beaten egg yolks. Stir in Cool Whip. Take 1/2 cake and pinch in bowl, 1/2 mixture, 1/2 candy, then repeat cake mixture and candy. Keep refrigerated.

title: petite meat ball-butter barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk and seasonings; mix and shape to form 1 inch balls.
Brown meat balls in butter.
Pour barbecue sauce over and simmer 10 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in greased oblong pan. Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Add olive oil to pot.
Add stewed tomatoes and crush fine. Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour, stirring often.
Spoon on pizza shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add toppings; cook for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: pinwheel potato candy
directions: Mash baked potato (remove skin) with a fork, leaving no lumps. Add confectioners sugar, a little at a time.
This mixture will become watery, so keep adding the sugar.
Once mixture is firm, but no longer sticky, roll flat (as you would biscuits).
Spread the peanut butter to a desired thickness.
Roll into a long log and slice 3/4-inch pieces.
If you wish to make a larger amount, make more logs, but do not try to make a larger initial mixture.

title: homemade deep dish pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain off grease. Add onions and peppers. Add tomato sauce, pizza mix sauces and spices. Simmer 15 minutes. Heat oven to 425°.

Prepare dough. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan up both sides. Fill dough in bottom and up sides as far as you can. Cover bottom with half the cheese, then half meat sauce, then the other half of the cheese, then the remaining meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti bread
directions: Place yeast, 1 1/2 cups flour and rest of ingredients in mixing bowl. Stir to blend and let sit 20 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour.
Knead on floured board until smooth.

If using dough hook, add small amounts of flour as needed to make dough leave sides of bowl. Shape into loaf and let rise in warm place until doubled. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool on rack. Excellent with pasta dishes.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Pour fruit in greased pan.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs. Sprinkle over fruit, then pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 10-inch spring-form pan. Press cottage cheese through a fine strainer. In a large bowl, blend cottage cheese, cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, eggs and margarine. Add in flour, cornstarch, vanilla, almond and salt. Press graham cracker crust into bottom of pan. Pour other ingredients into pan. Bake for 1 hour. Leave in oven 1 hour and let cool. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: microwave squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; onion,
salt
and
pepper
to
taste.
Add Accent (2 dashes); cook
in
until tender in covered microwave dish. After cooking, drain
squash;
add 1 tablespoon butter. Mix cut up Velveeta cheese,
egg,
milk and Ritz crackers into squash.
Cook 10 minutes
in
microwave
on
High without lid. After cooking, take out
of
microwave
and
sprinkle
1/4 cup Velveeta cheese grated on top
and
put back into microwave on High until melted. Take out and ready to eat.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl until light.
Blend in eggs. Add cocoa, vanilla and mixture of soda and sour cream.
Sift in flour and salt.
Mix in 1 cup boiling water.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Dust with additional cocoa.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Invert onto wire rack.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well with mixer.
Chill for 5 minutes in freezer. Meanwhile, whip cream until soft peaks form.
Remove from freezer; fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup of pudding mixture into bottom of a punch bowl (or 2 1/2-quart glass bowl).
Add vanilla wafers on top of pudding, then layer with sliced bananas.
Continue layering, ending with vanilla wafers.
Keep chilled until serving time.
This makes a large, rich pudding!

title: pepper steak with red wine
directions: Cut meat into thin strips and season with garlic, oregano, basil and onion powder.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Add sliced onions and sliced green peppers.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine remaining ingredients, except oil.
Add to meat mixture and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: country style beef and noodles
directions: Cover chuck roast (and bay leaf) with water in Dutch oven and cook until meat falls apart.
Remove from water and cool.
Flake roast and skim grease from water.
Add meat, vegetables and seasonings to taste.
Cook until vegetables are almost done, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add noodles and cook until done.
A cornstarch/water paste may be added to thicken.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Combine flour, oregano, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken breast with flour; combine.
Spray large skillet for 3 seconds with Pam. Saute garlic; add chicken breasts to saute on both sides until golden.
Add wine, broth and water; cook until done.
Add lemon slices.
Garnish with fresh, chopped parsley.

title: hot cheese bread
directions: Slice the bread long ways. Mix oleo, mayonnaise, and chopped peppers and spread on bread. Then cover with shredded cheese. Bake at 350 until cheese is melted and edges of bread is golden brown.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites; add 1/4 cup of the sugar, beat until stiff and set aside.
Cream the shortening, salt, remaining sugar and egg yolks; beat until creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture with the milk.
Fold in the beaten egg whites and floured blueberries.
Turn into well-greased square pan (9 x 9-inch pan);
sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch for 35
directions: Mix well. Freeze some of the mixture to keep punch cool without diluting.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: cheesy vegetable omelet
directions: Coat a 6-inch skillet with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add green pepper, onion and pimiento. Saute until tender.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine orange slices, dates, nuts and coconut with 1/2 cup of flour.
Cream butter and sugar well and then add eggs one at a time.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon soda with buttermilk and add alternately with the flour.
Add the candy and nut mixture and pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour the icing over it while hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Combine all of the ingredients except for the French onions, Cheddar cheese, and mashed potatoes.
Stir together well.
Then mix together
the mashed potatoes, Cheddar cheese and half of the can of French onions.
Spread evenly around the edge of the dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Then take out and put the remaining French onions on the top and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: white icing
directions: Whip shortening (Crisco) and butter.
Beat well.
Add gradually the 10x sugar and milk.
This stores well.
You may freeze this, thaw and use later.

title: beef soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot.
Add beef, bouillon cubes and tomato sauce; simmer for 2 hours.
Remove beef from pot.
Add vegetables, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
While vegetables are simmering, shred beef. Add shredded beef and orzo to pot, cook 15 minutes, until orzo is done.

title: spoon bread
directions: Butter casserole dish and keep warm.
Boil water.
Slowly add cornmeal and salt.
Cook and stir one minute.
Remove from heat. Add well beaten eggs and milk.
Add sugar and baking powder.
Pour in casserole.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: sourdough french bread starter
directions: Bring to boil milk, water and oil.
Cool to warm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add together.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir in flour, just until mixed.
Cover and let stand in warm place for 12 to 18 hours to sour.
Store in tightly closed container in refrigerator for several days.
Measure the amount needed and bring to room temperature before using.
Makes enough starter for 12 loaves.

title: mexican panocha
directions: Stir together the sugar, cream and salt and cook to soft ball stage (235°).
Just before removing from the stove, add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Do not stir while hot.
Cool to lukewarm and then beat until changes color.
Pour into greased pan.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Stir in ketchup, celery, lemon juice, vinegar, water and sugar.
Add turkey.
Lightly sprinkle with oregano.
Stir and cover.
Simmer and stir occasionally for 30 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Put macaroni in baking dish.
Add Spam, mushroom soup and mushrooms (drained).
Lay cheese strips on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts, then mix together good.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions in oil.
Drain and add salt and pepper. Stir in catsup and tomato sauce, stirring until all is mixed well. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan or 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with cheese and top with biscuits.
Bake 425° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: terry's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package. Drain and cool.
Place in casserole dish; blend in sour cream and onion soup mix.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Do not cover.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna dill spread
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use as sandwich filling or spread on crackers.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups.

title: lasagna mexicana
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, Mexibeans and green chillies.
Layer half of the tortillas on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Spread half of meat mixture over and sprinkle with half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in rolls.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Cut and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 55 to 60 minutes longer or until filling is set.
Cool completely on wire rack before cutting. Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage-rice vegetable medley
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a Dutch oven and mix until well blended.
Cover and simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Combine ham, onion, cheese and dried parsley in bowl.
In separate bowl, beat together egg, milk and oil.
Add 2 cups baking mix and blend well.
Add ham mixture, stirring until mixed.
Add remaining 1 cup baking mix, stirring until well blended.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in the bottom of a casserole dish coated with Pam.
Top with sliced olives and boiled eggs, then pour undiluted soup over the layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until the crumbs are lightly browned and the casserole is bubbly on top (about 25 minutes).

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and 1 3/4 gallons water; chill. Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in a 375° oven for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel crispies
directions: Unwrap caramels and place in 2-quart bowl.
Add butter and water.
Place in microwave oven.
Cook caramel mixture at High 4 minutes, stirring well every few minutes.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Press evenly into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Makes 36 squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Mix crushed cornflakes with 1/2 cup melted butter or oleo and sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lacey's homemade heavenly brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs together.
In another bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt, then mix all together slowly.
Add vanilla, then add pecans.
Grease pan; bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix well.
Add 1 carton whipped topping and you may add 1 cup chopped
nuts.
Put
in
graham
cracker crust or baked pastry crust.
Chill and serve.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and cheese. Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme.
Cut into bite size pieces for a wonderful appetizer.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mold into crust in a 9-inch pie pan.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture.
Add nuts. Bake in a moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer, garlic powder and black pepper in water until chicken is cooked.
Bone and set aside.
Reserve broth.
In separate pan, saute celery, bell pepper and onion in oleo.
Set aside.
In reserved broth, combine Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Bring to boil and add seashell noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add sauteed vegetables and boned chicken. Melt 1/2 pound Velveeta and add to noodle mixture.
Put into casserole dish and cover with remaining Velveeta.
Bake uncovered at 350° until cheese melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: puppy chow(best of fair)
directions: Pour cereal in large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minute or until melted smooth.
Stir for 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture, stirring constantly and carefully so all pieces are covered but not broken.
Pour cereal in Ziploc bag containing powdered sugar and shake.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add poppy seed to dry ingredients and mix with before mentioned ingredients.
Roll into little balls.
Flatten with bottom of flat glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mam's buttermilk white cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add all sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold in the egg whites. Bake in 2 layers in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Put layers together with Lemon Filling.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit; add water, if necessary, to make 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add cola and fruit.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with salad dressing, cream cheese dressing or whipped cream.

title: brunswick stew(georgia-not maine!)
directions: Boil fryers; cool; pick meat from bones.
Leave 1 inch broth in pot.
Add onions, ground beef and pork to broth in pot.
Cook until done.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and potatoes.
Cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add salt, pepper and hot sauce to taste.
Add 1 to 2 bay leaves.
Cook about 2 additional hours (slowly).
Add tomato paste; stirring occasionally.
This makes a lot! Use large stock pot; freezes great.
(When spoon stands alone this is thick enough.)

title: mr. p's vegetable salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Put in bowl and cover with vinegar.
Marinate 1 hour. Drain green beans, peas, carrots and pimento.
In a large bowl, toss together vegetables and cooked macaroni.

title: southern smothered prawns
directions: Devein and wash prawns.
Preheat large skillet with Wesson oil or vegetable oil.
Slowly brown prawns and pour off the oil.
Add the tomato puree.
Stir in all the seasonings.
Cook at low temperature for 15 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 6 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan in oven. Mix all ingredients (including margarine after melting) together. Bake at 350° for 45 - 55 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Make white sauce with flour, butter and milk.
Add corn, salt and sugar.
Cook until hot.
Mix in bread crumbs and egg.
Bake slowly at 275°.

title: apricot cheese delight
directions: Drain and chill fruit. Reserve juice. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add to fruit juice. Reserve remainder of fruit juice for topping. Chill until slightly congealed. Fold in fruit and marshmallows. Pour into baking dish. Chill until firm. Spread with fruit cheese topping.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in saucepan over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter, vanilla and raw oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; let cool.
Immediately place cookies in an airtight container; this will keep them moist.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned in a 350° oven.

title: ono ulu
directions: Boil or steam
cook
ulu and cut into bite size pieces, 1/2-inch thick.
In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine. Add in ulu;
fry,
coating ulu with butter.
Stir in honey and brown sugar, mixing well.
Add in brandy and mix.
Serve hot.

title: five-layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle on nuts, followed by chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned. Remove to a rack and let cool completely before cutting.
Makes 36 bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; save juice for making Jell-O,
also the syrup from the drained pineapple tidbits or chunks.
Put mayonnaise in dish; add pineapple and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, diced unpared red or green apple and sliced banana.

title: ground turkey mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients
together except for 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Bake
in
a
loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top after it is baked.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add slowly 2 cups Wesson oil while beating until thick.
Add 1 small onion and 2 tablespoons poppy seed.

title: green bean lucette
directions: Alternate layers of green beans and onion rings.
Mix rest of ingredients, all but cheese and paprika, in a bowl and pour over beans and onion rings.
Grate enough cheese to cover mix and then sprinkle paprika over the cheese.
Bake in a shallow casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and shortening.
Remove from heat and add raisins and almonds.
Drop onto waxed paper and cool.
Makes 2 dozen.
Store in refrigerator.

title: petal bread
directions: In warm water, dissolve yeast, let stand few minutes.
Add salt, sugar, egg and shortening.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, stir thoroughly.
Add 1 1/4 cups more flour or more.
Knead 10 minutes. Let rise until double.
Work down.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into diamonds, dip each in melted butter or oleo and place in Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.
If angel food pan is used, put pan in 9-inch cake pan or oleo will leak out in oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into 9 inch pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 450° then reduce to 375° and bake until mixture is firm.

title: barbara's bean casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Drain liquid from butter beans and shelled beans.
Put the 3 kinds of beans into 1 3/4 to 2-quart bean pot or casserole.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sage turkey meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together all of the ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until browned.
This recipe can be made in half.

title: platski-potato pancakes
directions: Blend all ingredients, except oil, together (should be a little thicker than pancakes).
Heat oil in frying pan.
Pour batter in oil; brown on each side.
When finished, serve with sour cream and applesauce.

title: 5-minute double layer chocolate pie
directions: Beat milk, pudding and 1/2 of the whipped topping in medium bowl with wire whisk 1 minute. Spread in crust. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding layer in crust. Enjoy immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve. Garnish as desired.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Grind vanilla wafers and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 325° in 3 layers.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 2/3 cup sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes and cool.
Add butter and vanilla extract.
Pour into baked shell and spread with meringue made with egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If desired, add 1 cup coconut to filling and sprinkle some on top.

title: lime and pear salad
directions: Let jello and hot water firm up a little (not completely). Blend softened cream cheese with jello.
Add 1 small and 1 large can of pears.
Cut the halves in about 3 pieces.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together.
Add eggs, butter, and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes until filling is set. Cool completely before serving.

title: christmas candy
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.
You put candy thermometer tip in pan.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute onion in Dutch oven until transparent.
Add water and broccoli.
Simmer until broccoli is tender.
Add salmon and bouillon granules.
Combine evaporated milk, flour and milk. Season to taste.
Heat until chowder thickens slightly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute, but do not brown onion in margarine.
Remove onion to a small bowl.
Saute rice until it turns yellow, then add onions, water chestnuts, beef consomme and grated carrots.
Cover and bake about 40 minutes at 375°.

title: apricot chicken breast
directions: Mix yogurt, mustard and jam. Pour over chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Form into balls.
Roll into coconut and powdered sugar.

title: tandy take cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and oil.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed from the oven, spread with 1 1/4 cups peanut butter.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
When firm, melt Crisco and chocolate bar.
Spread over peanut butter and cool again in refrigerator.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix ingredients and form long rolls, 1-inch in diameter.
When ready to bake, slice into 1/4-inch rounds and bake 5 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Place cut up rhubarb in baking pan.
Boil sugar, vanilla, flour and water together and pour over rhubarb.

title: stir-fry beef with tomatoes
directions: Freeze steak for 30 minutes, then slice diagonally across grain in 1/8-inch thick slices.
In 2-cup glass measure combine sugar, soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Pour over sliced meat in medium bowl.
Marinate at least 30 minutes, turning meat after 15 minutes. Heat microwave browning dish for 6 minutes or until very hot. Remove meat from marinade, reserving extra.
Add oil and meat; microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High, stirring halfway through cooking. Add green peppers and onion.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Top with tomato wedges.
In a 1-cup glass measure combine cornstarch, water and remaining marinade.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes more.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Serve on cooked rice.

title: wicky wacky cake(no egg)
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Combine all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and salt slowly.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 10-inch cookie pan leaving 1 inch on sides.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until brown.
Place Hershey bars on top immediately upon removal from oven.
Spread as they melt.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Allow to cool and cut to size cookie desired.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add other ingredients except Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or a glass bowl.
Top with Cool Whip and fresh strawberries if desired.
Freeze.
Thaw 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: lentil soup
directions: Put all in a pot and cook for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder and spices.
Fold together. Spread on greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except onion rings.
Place in lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle French fried onion rings on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: deep dish chicago style pizza
directions: Let loaf of frozen bread dough thaw and rise to double in size. Punch down and put in greased deep dish pizza pan (14-inches in diameter and 2-inches deep).
Let ball of dough rise in pan for 10 minutes.
Then work the dough by pushing with fingers until completely covers bottom of pan.
Pull the edge up to form a lip or border crust of dough.
Cover pan with towel and let rise 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Prick crust with tines of fork and bake it at 475° for 4 minutes exactly.
Then brush crust with olive oil.

title: bonnie's baked beans
directions: Mix together in 2-quart casserole and bake until hot.
These are more barbecue flavored and less sweet than regular baked beans.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1/2-quart container, stir together 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup white corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup roasted, salted peanuts*; peanuts should be mixed in well. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Quickly pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or unbuttered nonstick coated cookie sheet. Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix dry gelatin with other ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and gel. Cook the pineapple and apricot juice, sugar, flour, egg and butter until thick. When cool, add the whipped cream. Spread over the firm gelatin mix and top with grated cheese.

title: monkey biscuit bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Shake each piece of biscuit in mixture.
Put 1/2 of a pecan on each piece and place face down in well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt 1 stick of butter and 1/2 cup white sugar.
Bring to light boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs, then add milk, coconut, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: basic red chile sauce(made from red chili powder.)
directions: Heat shortening in a stainless steel saucepan over medium heat. Stir in flour to a paste consistency.
Cook until golden brown. Add red chili powder and cook for an additional minute.
Add cold water gradually and stir constantly so that lumps do not form.
Add seasonings.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Use in any recipe calling for red chile sauce.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter with salt and sugar.
Add orange juice.
Add eggs. Sift together and add flour, soda and baking powder alternating with sour milk. Drop by small spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° to 400° oven until edges are slightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: nancy's congealed red applesauce
directions: Cook red hots in 1 cup water until melted.
Dissolved gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Mix red hot mixture with gelatin.
Cool.
Add 1 cup applesauce.
Place in refrigerator and let set until firm. Top with Cool Whip.

title: mushroom balls
directions: Mince mushrooms.
Mix with cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt. Unroll crescent rolls.
Pinch seams together to make rectangles. Spread mushroom mixture and roll as you would a jelly roll.
Cut roll into pieces (10 to 12 for every 2 rolls).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: century punch
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Heat and bring to a boil.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serves 50.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt ingredients until smooth.
Pour over 18 ounces Golden Graham cereal.
Stir until coated.
Put 1 1/2 pounds powdered sugar into a large (turkey size) plastic baking bag.
Add cereal mixture.
Shake bag, turning, separating and coating cereal.
Add more sugar if it is still sticky.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions. Add beans and taco mix.
Combine soup and Ro-Tel in another bowl.
Layer beef and bean mixture, soup mixture, cheese and tortillas in casserole dish.
Add black olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Pick over beans, discarding bad ones.
Rinse well. Place ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover with 2 quarts water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.
More water may be needed.
Remove meat from bone; discard bone and bay leaves.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
(If salt is added to beans during cooking, beans will not cook to desired consistency.)
Freezes very well.

title: holiday chocolate butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients except flour and cocoa.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour and cocoa until well mixed.
Shape into desired shape, 1 inch balls, 2 or 3 inch logs or balls flattened with cookie press.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour vegetables in dish.
Melt Cheez Whiz and 1/2 stick oleo over low heat and pour over vegetables. Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick oleo and sprinkle over vegetables and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cook noodles and drain well.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Place in baking pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Cut potatoes into wedges.
Pour over potatoes.
Place skin side down in broiler pan.
Bake at 375°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered, or until golden brown.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt tidbits in double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Mix well. Drop on wax paper.

title: basic waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery and nuts.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream.
Gently fold into apple mixture.
Serves 6.

title: white pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs together and add gradually the milk, flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 2 layers and use any filling desired.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Mix zucchini, butter or margarine and seasonings in a skillet. Cover and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking, turning slices, until barely tender, about 5 minutes more. Sprinkle with cheese while hot.
Serves 4.

title: chop suey cake
directions: In large bowl (do not use mixer or processor) combine flour, sugar, eggs, soda, pineapple and juice, walnuts and coconut.
Mix with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bongo bongo banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a blender jar, combine apple juice concentrate and raisins.
Puree until raisins are completely chopped.
Pour this mixture into a large mixing bowl; add the mashed banana, oil and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add the flours, wheat germ, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Mix thoroughly. Coat a loaf pan with vegetable cooking spray and spoon in the batter, spreading it evenly.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes, until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese and pineapple.
Add marshmallows.
Mix, then fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: seafood and pasta salad(serves 8)
directions: Poach fillets in 1-inch boiling water 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove fillets with slotted spoon and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl; blend until smooth.
Cut cooked fish into 1-inch pieces; stir into macaroni mixture.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
There are 224 calories per serving.

title: steak dinner
directions: Place steak on foil.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and cream of mushroom soup or fresh mushrooms.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over sirloin.
Add butter.
Wrap good in foil and bake in oven at 375° for 2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Put 1/2 of cheese in batter and 1/2 on top.
Add 1 large onion.
Mix.
Bake in a large iron skillet at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot garlic bread
directions: Cut a loaf of French bread into 3/4-inch slices, not quite through bottom crust.
Combine margarine, garlic, parsley, oregano and dill.
Spread mixture generously between slices.
Wrap loosely in foil; heat in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, including crackers.
Add oil and shake well in covered bowl.
Place in sealed container and let stand.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and other ingredients in order given.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 quarts of water and 1 teaspoon salt until tender, for about 15 minutes.
Pour into colander and rinse away starch with warm water.
Arrange layers each of macaroni and cheese in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar; set aside.
In small pan, mix together the vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt. Bring to a rolling boil; cool slightly.
Pour over cabbage mixture; stir well.
Makes enough to fill 2 quart jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter and sugars, add pudding in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture stir well.
Add oatmeal and nuts or chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: martha washington chocolates
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to sugar and add milk.
Blend well.
Then add nuts and coconut.
Shape into small-sized balls.
Refrigerate.

title: five layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, bacon, onion, eggs and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread over salad.
Sprinkle with cheese and chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put coconut and pecans in bottom.
Prepare cake mix per directions.
Pour on top of pecans and coconut.

title: nellie's fruit salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.	Just before serving, add two sliced bananas.
Strawberries can also be added.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook until clear 1 cup water, cornstarch and sugar.
Add dry peach jello and continue cooking until jello dissolves (approximately 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and add ice water. Refrigerate until mixture thickens.
This takes quite awhile but never fear, it will thicken.
Fold fresh peaches into thickened mixture and place into already baked pie shell.
Can substitute strawberry jello and fresh strawberries for strawberry pie.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until brown; drain off excess fat. Separate rolls and pat in pizza pan with points toward center. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle potatoes and top with cheese. In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake in 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Bring Crisco, water, butter and cocoa to boil in saucepan. After mixture has boiled, pour over dry ingredients. Mix well. Add eggs, soda, cinnamon, buttermilk and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pare and coarsely grate potatoes and onion.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper and mix well.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Drop potato batter by heaping tablespoon into skillet.
Saute until golden brown and crisp on bottom, turn and cook until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: lasagna ragu
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook noodles in boiling water for 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in a shallow 3-quart baking dish, alternating layers of noodles, meat, cheese and sauce. Add grated cheese last.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Stir in oatmeal.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Leave in pan.
Spread on frosting and broil until lightly browned.

title: canned pole beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot, then cover with water. Boil, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add hot water as needed.
Do not let them boil dry.
When done, pour into jars.
Water from pot should cover beans in jars.
Seal with lid and let cool.
When ready to eat, rinse beans well under cold tap water.
Place in iron pot with seasoned meat and cover with water.
Cook on low heat with lid until almost dry.

title: microwave mini pizza snacks
directions: Arrange muffins on paper plate.
Spread with spaghetti sauce. Top with cheese and season with oregano.
Cook at Medium 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: u. s. navy cannon fodder(chili)
directions: Brown meat. Pour off water. Add other ingredients except beans. Cook over medium heat for 8 hours, then add beans.
Cook 2 more hours.
Eat with caution!

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add condensed milk; mix well.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla. Separate into 3 equal parts, 1 red, 1 green and 1 natural.
Layer the red first, then the green, then the natural layer.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cream the butter; gradually add sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; stir in the flour.
Blend in dates and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes, or until light brown.
Cool; shake date balls inside of plastic bag with 1/2 cup powdered sugar in it.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound flour into steak.
Cut into cubes and brown in butter. When done, remove from pan, put in onions.
Cook the onions slowly (about 5 minutes).
Put meat back in, add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Heat until warm.
Add to cooked noodles, mix and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: thanksgiving garden relish
directions: Yields about 5 pints.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg and butter together until it forms a crumbly mixture. Pour into pie shell.

Pour evaporated milk over mixture. Pour equal amounts of half and half and whole milk into pie shell until shell is full. Bake at 425° until brown crust forms over top, about 20 to 25 minutes. Gently break crust with a rubber spatula.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer or until pie begins to thicken.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter, sugar and curry powder and bring to boil. Drain fruit and arrange in baking dish, dotting with cherries. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until bubbling.

title: brownie mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix cocoa and sugar.
Put all in a Fix and Mix bowl and cut in shortening. Store in plastic sealed canister.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Bake at 400° until brown in cornbread pan.

title: aunt susie's delicious punch
directions: Mix jello, water, and pineapple juice and freeze.
When you are ready to serve, let this mixture thaw for about 30 minutes and pour Sprite over it.

title: simmering potpourri(do not eat - just for scent)
directions: Allow apples, orange rind and cranberries to air dry (or in low oven or in dehydrator).
Mix all ingredients.

title: peanut butter coconut crisps
directions: Mix flour and
baking soda.
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugar in a	large
bowl
with electric mixer until fluffy. Beat in egg and honey.
With mixer on low speed gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in coconut.
Divide dough
in thirds.
Roll each into a log 5 1/2-inches long and 1 1/2-inches thick.
Wrap each tightly and refrigerate 6 hours or
overnight. Heat
oven	to
Lightly
grease
cookie sheets.
With
a very sharp knife, slice 1 log at a time (keep rest	refrigerated) in	1/4-inch
thick rounds.
Place 1-inch apart
on
prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until
lightly
browned. Cool
on
sheet 1 minute.	Remove to rack	to
cool
completely. Store
loosely covered.
Makes 72 cookies.

title: final exam brownies
directions: Mix sugar and melted butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and vanilla; then add marshmallows and nuts.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour in a generously greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the 1/2 cup chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix together dates, salt, baking soda and boiling water and let stand.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add date mixture to sugar-shortening mixture and mix well.
Use 5 (Number 2) cans (don't grease); fill half full.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: quick barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in a skillet; salt and pepper.
Pour catsup over chicken; cover with Coke.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until liquid is almost gone.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Prepare broccoli, as suggested and drain.
Add onion and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
Mix soup and cheese together. Warm while vegetables cooking.
Drain vegetables.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with soup/cheese mixture.
Brown in oven at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
May top with buttered bread crumbs, onion rings, etc.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2
greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: In 3 quart
saucepan,
cook
cinnamon
candies in water until dissolved.	Add apples
and cook slowly, uncovered, just until tender, about 15
to
minutes,	turning
once during cooking. Refrigerate apples	in
syrup several hours, turning once.	(As the apples stand,
they absorb the bright red color of the candies.) Blend
together
cream cheese, milk and lemon juice until smooth and creamy.
Add pineapple, dates and nuts. Drain apples.
Stuff centers with cream cheese mixture.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: speedy chili
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; cook until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: sauerkraut & apple salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and then drizzle oil over all. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach and tear into bite sized pieces.
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble into small pieces.
Cook peas and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours or more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients.
Cook on very low heat several hours.
Stir frequently.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: salt fried potatoes
directions: Place in skillet and cover.
Cook over low heat until soft.

title: morning french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 tsp. cinnamon in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Add apples and raisins and toss well.
Spread apple mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Arrange slices of bread on top.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and remaining 2 tsp cinnamon until well blended.
Pour mixture over bread soaking completely.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, covered with foil, in preheated oven at 375 for 40 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 5 additional minutes until brown.

title: quick hurry bars
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts in medium bowl.
Add condensed milk; stir well.
Scrape into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes, until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool; cut and store covered (airtight).
Makes 25 squares.

title: peas and carrots in thyme sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion and thyme until onions are all tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Add peas and carrots.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover 8 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Makes 3 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° first 20 minutes, covered with foil.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 more minutes.

title: the house dressing
directions: Place all the ingredients, except oil, in a blender and mix well.
Add oil and blend.
Serve on greens or citrus salad.
A slice hard-boiled egg and fried crumbled bacon may be added to top of green salad.

title: curried goat
directions: Wash meat off and trim off fat.
Drain off excess water.
Cut celery in very small pieces.
Add all the ingredients to meat and marinate overnight.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and butter.
Put in a greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Crumble crackers over mixture.
Dot with butter pats.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: gina's caponato
directions: Soak eggplant in water for 30 minutes; drain.
Heat oil in 10 or 12-inch pan.
Fry cubes until soft.
Remove from pan; place in casserole dish.
If needed, add more oil and saute onions, peppers and celery for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for another 15 minutes.
Pour over eggplant and stir gently.
(Served as a vegetable dish or put up in glass and served cold as a salad.)

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in chunks, approximately 1-inch cubes in size.
Beat egg. Add milk and enough flour to thicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Dip the eggplant cubes thoroughly, coating them heavily.
Drop in hot oil and fry until golden brown. Be careful not to burn. Drain and eat while hot.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Brown chicken in non-stick skillet. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken. Simmer 1 hour until sauce is thick. Be sure to get all glaze on chicken.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and save broth.
Cook onions and pepper in a skillet until tender.
Mix soups, onion, pepper, chili powder and garlic.
Add tomatoes and chicken.
Place tortillas in hot broth to heat.
Layer tortillas in casserole dish.
Add chicken mixture, cheese and tortillas in layers with the top layer being the tortillas.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: emily's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips at low speed until thoroughly moistened. Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape dough into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until top appears cracked.
Cool 2 minutes, remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 32 cookies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make pastry for 1 crust pie.
Line pie pan.
Pour into pie pan.
(For crispness, have bottom pastry a little thicker than 1/8-inch.)
Bake just until a silver knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean.
The center may still look soft, but will set later.
Serve slightly warm or cold.
Bake at 425° (hot oven).
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk. Beat until real fluffy.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Finish filling freezer with whole milk.
Ready to place in electric or hand crank freezer.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar. Add eggs, flavorings, vinegar and food coloring. Mix dry ingredients separately, sifting all together. Add alternately with buttermilk and sugar mixture. Beat thoroughly. Bake in three 9-inch round layer pans (greased and dusted with flour). Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scandinavian meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, bread, milk, onion, egg, salt and pepper. Mix well and form into balls.
Brown in skillet or oven.
Drain off all grease.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and tomato sauce all together and shape into loaf.
Place in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over meat loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers. Mix in crackers.
Chill overnight.
Enjoy!

title: pistachio pudding delight
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into salad bowl.
Top with nuts. Chill several hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion, pepper and butter until soft. Mash squash and mix with sour cream and soup.
Line dish with 1/2 herb dressing.
Pour in squash mixture and top with remaining dressing. Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: mama's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Can be served cold or warmed in the microwave.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Take one piece of bread; put a piece of cheese on top.
Put in toaster oven until bread is toasted and cheese is melted.
Good with a cold glass of milk.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 370° for 40 to 50 minutes. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Bake in a Bundt pan or angel food pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, flour and coconut.
Mix well; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Put apples into 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and salt.
Blend sugar, flour and butter.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or microwave, uncovered, for 12 minutes on High.

title: chili soup
directions: In a large deep saucepan, brown beef in oil, turning to brown on all sides.
Add beef broth and simmer 1 hour.
Add peppers, onion, garlic, chili powder, cumin, tomatoes and beans.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Blend in 1/2 cup of cheese; heat until the cheese melts.
Garnish with remaining cheese before serving. Makes 6 servings, each with 398 calories, 19g of fat and 86mg of cholesterol.

title: simple swiss steak
directions: In a bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion. Shape firmly into patties. In skillet over medium heat, cook a few patties at a time until brown on each side. Spoon off fat. Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms. Return patties to skillet. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tests done, turning occasionally.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring to boil vinegar and sugar.
Add oil, salt and pepper. Pour this over mixture of all other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Combine margarine and milk with other ingredients.
Pour over fruit (apples, peaches, strawberries, etc.).
Bake in dish at 350° until done.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cocoa and vegetable oil.
Add sugar and eggs; mix.
Add milk and vanilla, then flour, and then boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased cake pan, and bake about 30 minutes (or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).

title: janet's meatballs
directions: Pour over meatballs.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: frogmoor stew
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large 6 to 8-quart pot. Bring to boiling and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add corn and sausage; bring back to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; bring back to boil and cook until shrimp are bright pink.
Drain and serve with hot hush puppies.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Wash the vegetables.
Cut and put in a big pot.
Add water and tomato juice; boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add bouillon and butter. Simmer 30 minutes more.
Eat!

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Whip together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Crush Oreos (I put in food processor or Ziploc bag and use rolling pin).
Add cream cheese mixture to pudding.
Use a flowerpot lined with foil.
Layer the cookies and pudding mixture about 4 times, ending with a generous cookie layer.
Put in a silk flower or two and have fun!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and celery; cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and spread in a casserole dish.
Combine Velveeta cheese, milk and flour in a saucepan; stir over low heat until smoothly blended.
Pour cheese sauce over cabbage.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly (start watching carefully after 30 minutes of baking!).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed of electric mixer.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with beaten eggs to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll on floured board until very thin and cut with a cookie cutter. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until light brown.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, egg yolks and water. Beat at medium speed until just combined. Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture; mix just until moistened. Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into batter. Spoon batter into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Immediately invert layers on wire racks. Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans. Cool completely. Spread Creamy Coconut Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Garnish with pecan halves.

title: slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt, let stand for 2 hours.
Boil vinegar, water, and sugar for 1 minute. Set aside to cool.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Mix water, coffee and sugar.
Stir well until all is dissolved.
Add 1 quart vodka.
Add 2 tablespoons vanilla; mix well.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: texas trash pickles
directions: Soak squash, pepper and onion in the gallon of water and salt. Cover with ice.
Let stand 2 hours; drain well.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drop pickles in hot liquid and bring to a hard boil again.
Pack in jars.
Cover with hot liquid and seal.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Put in casserole.
Cover with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs or crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain chicken.
Add to cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into ball. Roll into chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, flour and soda.
Fold in beaten egg whites (stiff, but not dry), mace, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Bake in a greased, lightly floured tube pan in 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Invert pan on plate until cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Into 7 x 11 or 9 x 13-inch pan, place asparagus on bottom, then peas and water chestnuts.
Pour soup over mixture.
Roll bread fingers in melted margarine.
Place on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Combine pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges, dry pudding, and whipped topping.
Mix well and chill.
Sprinkle nuts over top before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix white sugar and flour, then mix all other ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook until thick.
Pour over cooked sliced sweet potatoes and bake 30 minutes at 350°, until candied.

title: dip for chips
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, minced onion, dill weed and seasoned salt well and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients over low heat until well combined and having the consistency of thin gravy, approximately 1 hour.

title: homemade catsup
directions: Put tomatoes in big pot or pan; boil with onions and garlic until soft.
